(459, 4, '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><b>Run:</b> #4 - </span>Oct 1st -</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Location: </span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">&nbsp;</span><place><placetype><span style="COLOR: black">Forest</span></placetype><span style="COLOR: black">&nbsp;</span><placename><span style="COLOR: black">Edge</span></placename><span style="COLOR: black">&nbsp;</span><placetype><span style="COLOR: black">Elementary School</span></placetype></place><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Hares:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">  14 Karat Cock, Cunning Runt, The Clorox Kid, and Just Tony</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">FRB:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Shellacking the Bishop (if you show up next week, you get a prize for being such an overacheiver)</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">FBI:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">  Vominatrix</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">DFL: </span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Mini Barbarino and Crew</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Virgins:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">  Elissa, Dan, Melissa, Veronica, and Jenny</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Visitors:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Sister’s on Top, Dumb Blond, Nippoless Cage, and Paper or Plastic</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black"> <p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Hashit: </span></b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Obese Wan Kenobe, for </span><span style="COLOR: black">getting lost and not ever making circle.<p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black"> <p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black">Trash:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            When I got to the school a little after </span><time minute="0" hour="18"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">6:00pm</span></time><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, the hares and a few other hashers were already there.  The one that actually comes to mind is <b>Obese Wan Kenobe</b>.  He casually asked <b>Cunning Runt</b> how long trail would be tonight.  She laughed and said, “Two hours—max.”  He laughed it off and thought nothing else of it…until he became so lost on trail (was he even on trail?) that he just ended up going back to start to wait for us to finish.  Well, looks like someone’s keeping the hashit one more week!</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            We circled up, 5 minutes late only because I thought traffic was bad and I wanted to give everyone a chance to get there on time (there’s really no helping Land Ho and Paper or Plastic).  But I’m glad I held off because I did see the cousins, Just <b>Melissa</b> and Just <b>Jolanta</b> and Just <b>Jennifer</b> with her virgin/my roommate, Just <b>Jenny</b> in tow.  So hares were away, we met our visitors, and we introduced the virgins.  Then we circled up again.  Seems someone forgot to do Father Abraham.  That same someone also doesn’t know her left from her right.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            12 minutes later and we were walking.  The running wankers took off ahead of us on the macadam (that means “asphalt trail”…thank you <b>Cunning Runt</b>), but then we split for a short cut and got back on the runners trail.  <b>Bad Dog</b> had the flashlight of all flashlights.  Seriously, if you didn’t see this thing, you have to…he was landing planes while we were on trail, I kid not.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            We met up with <b>The Clorox Kid</b> at the beer check.  It was obvious that he was merely a flour mule.  He was 