"COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><b>FBI:</b>  Porta Potter and Just Diana</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><b>Virgins:</b>          Jennifer Doolin and Tony Simms</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><b>Visitors:</b>         Pencil Dick and Just Brian</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><b>Hashit:</b> Just Stephanie, for not taking 14K seriously (but who can blame her?)</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black"><font face="Times New Roman"><b>Trash:</b><p /></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Man did I have a blast at the last sh*t hash. Look, I’m a poet and did not even know it. I knew it was going to be an interesting night when I try to send the Hares (<b>FOC</b>, <b>AndHowsHerBush</b>, <b>Mini</b> and <b>Chastity</b>) away to start laying trail when Tupperware informs me they still have 5 minutes. I look at her and say what time you got she says “5 till 7” I inform her that her watch is WRONG, but being the nice person I am I tell her fine they have 5 minutes. But then low and behold <b>Field of Cream</b> comes whining to me that the Hares are ready to go and I’m thinking wait this is the Hash we NEVER start on time and go talk to <b>Tupperware</b> her watch works differently then mine. So Hares away promptly at </span><time minute="0" hour="19"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">7pm</span></time><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, actually </span><time minute="5" hour="19"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">5 after 7</span></time><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, depends on whose watch you looked at. So there I am out in the middle of nowhere, actually I was in the middle of Wolf Trap but it felt like the middle of nowhere. I’m running with <b>Obese</b> and he takes off, without a flashlight I might add. He would later regret not having a flashlight but that is another story to be told later over an ICE COLD BEER. <b>Porta Potter</b> and Just <b>Diane</b> are in front of me as we are going up this hill. I said sh*t I hate hills and Just <b>Diane</b> says “that’s not a hill” “we ran up hills twice as long and twice as steep when I was training”. I’m thinking training? Training for what? But I hate hills and I can barely breathe as I run up this damn hill, let alone ask her about her training. I’m also thinking girl you have drunk too many shots at the last intersection to think this is NOT a damn hill. I got to tell ya I thought that was great idea to lay tiny shot bottles at all the intersections along trail. I do not ever remember seeing that many intersections on a trail. Anyway great job Hares with the Shots. Did Mini think of that? So I’m running and running and running and running thinking to myself what the hell am I doing? Wait that’s right I’m at the Hash. As it gets darker and darker and the flour appears to be less and less visible, I find myself in WATER up to my sac….AND I do not mean my flour sac. I’m thinking man is this water cold or what? Wait, I’m at the Hash the water would never be cold. At some point I stumble on and past the beer check. I vaguely remember hearing <b>14k</b> yell something about not going through a tunnel. I’m thinking tunnel? What tunnel? Fu** it…..So I keep running and running and running asked myself again what the hell am I doing? Wait I’m still at the hash….. I ran into Just <b>Norland</b> along the way in his GQ shoes….I’m thinking remember those shoes come naming time…..So as I continue to run and run and run and run I’m thinking of all the great names I can  come up for Just <b>Norland</b> and oh yeah I’m still at the hash. Finally I get to finish, the only folks not at finish are the walkers. I see <b>Haz Mattress</b>, who evidently went body surfing down some steps out in the middle of nowhere, err... I mean out in the middle of Wolf Trap sitting in the back of her truck nursing a beer and her ankle…..About an hour after I got in the walkers showed up. Just <b>Stephanie</b> is soaking wet and I asked what the deal was…She told me that though it was not the first Saturday of the month she decided to take a bath in the water the same not so cold water I referenced earlier, please reference SAC. This stunt got her the Hash Sh*t. I overheard Just <b>Shelley</b> tell someone that was the most fun she can ever remember having. Also wanted to mention my good friend <b>Airtight</b> who as always reminds me “DON’T BE UGLY” That’s about all I recall from the SECOND trail of the SH*T.  - <b>Hood Whorenament</b></span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">One Walking Wankers Perspective: What a Shitty Trail!!  The walking Wankers were on trail too long.  I think we all need a refresher course on items to bring to the Hash since 2 out of 8 remembered to bring a flashlight and might I add dry clothes!  We found our way to the amphitheater and found our map.  Trying to read the map wasn\'t as easy as I (<b>O-69</b>) thought and obviously didn\'t read it very well.  <b>Land Ho</b> and <b>Between a Rock</b> <b>and a Hard On</b> took off with one flashlight while the others, Just <b>Stephanie</b>, Just <b>Shelley</b>, Just <b>Jennifer</b>, <b>Airtight</b>, <b>O-69</b>,<b>Tupperware</b> followed what we thought was trail.  After going through a little creek the one and only flashlight died!! <b> Stephanie</b> decided to throw it into the creek and we could see the faint light still glowing.  <b>Airtight</b> decided to retrieve it just in case it might come back to life (it didn\'t).  On the other side now, pitch black we saw lights coming towards us!  Thank God it was <b>14K</b> and <b>Udder Ho</b>!  We followed them only to realize we were on long trail!  I know we slowed them down but they were real troopers!!  <b>14K</b> discovered the &quot;hidden hash” that was placed on the side of a hill and lead us to a very large creek.  <b>14K</b> warned us that it was up to his balls.  Just <b>Stephanie</b> went first and got stuck in the rocks making her fall down up to her shoulders in water.  Panic nearly set in and she did it again.  Needless to say the rest of the pack took caution in maneuvering the boulders under our feet.  There is so much more since we were on trail for and hour and a half but bottom line is that the Hares came back to find us and lead us into finish. For the record <b>Land Ho</b> and <b>Between a Rock and a Hard On</b> made into finish 20+ minutes before the rest of us and they didn\'t even have the map, go figure.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">By the time my virgin, <b>Just Jennifer</b> and I arrived, there was already a plethora of people milling about the huge parking lot at </span><place><placename><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">McLean</span></placename><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">&nbsp;</span><placename><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Bible</span></placename><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">&nbsp;</span><placetype><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Church</span></placetype></place><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">.  The beer, along with <b>O69, Hood Whorenament, and Airtight</b>, all arrived shortly thereafter to a thunderous applause from the crowd, who was of course, ready to down six or seven beers before getting on trail.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            After our standard 30 minute social hour, hares were away, virgins (<b>Just Jennifer and Just Tony</b>) and visitors (<b>Pencil Dick and Just Brian</b>) were introduced, and a rowdy “Father Abraham” was sung, we were WALKING!</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            Trail headed toward the enormous parking garage at the rear of the church.  <b>Haz Mattress</b> informed us that on Sundays, the garage houses 3.2 million cars, including the preacher’s BMW.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            Well, we got into the woods and <b>Haz Mattress</b> was down.  Not on her knees, but flat on her ass.  She had a nasty fall and twisted her ankle.  Thanks to our chivalrous hashers, <b>Just Kent and Pencil Dick</b>, I’m sure she’ll be just fine.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            The trail then split, taking the family wankers behind the Blair Witch Amphitheater and eventually across Route 7.  The runners and directionally challenged walkers went through the woods, down a creek, and to Wolf Trap before meeting back up with the walkers.  Thanks to <b>14K and The Udder Ho</b> for rescuing the damsels in distress (<b>Airtight, O69, Tupperware, Just Jennifer, Just Stephanie and Just Shelley</b>).  Next time lets remember our flashlights!</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            Circle was relatively short, although we got a late start.  Too many people sang “Hashers, meet the Hashers.”  Do us all a favor and get on to Global Trash (<a href="http://www.gthhh.com/"><span style="COLOR: blue">www.gthhh.com</span></a>) and download the hash hymnal!</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">            <b>And How’s Her Bush</b>, who is apparently haring every DC area hash for the next month, sent us all over to Mr. Smith’s (you know, by Night Dreams?) for a nice on-after.  Word has it that <b>AHHB</b> will also be haring next Tuesday.  Start is a Park View High School in Sterling (this is an alma mater for a few of us…).</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">                        <b>ON-ON!  Tupperware</b></span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></b><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">P.S.  We will be having a mis-management meeting at my new place sometime in the near future.  Join the mailing list (on the web page) to stay up to date.  ALL are welcome to attend and encouraged to bring fresh ideas…besides that, I’ll have beer.</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">P.S. again:  We still need hares, see <b>Mini Barbarino</b> to sign up!</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Violations:</span></b><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Departing Hasher:                       Chastity (going to Vermont!)</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Wearing a Pedometer:                Haz Mattress</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Late Sign-in:                                 Land-Ho (go figure)</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Super Bitch:                                  Tupperware</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Fashion Statement:                      Just Jennifer</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Safety Hazard:                              Just Tony</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          A Big F*ck You!:                           Hares</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Bathing on Trail:                           Just Stephanie</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          Body Surfing:                                Haz Mattress</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">          P.O.T:                                             Just Stephanie, Just Shelly, O69, and Just Tony</span><span style="COLOR: black"><p /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" /></span>', ''),
