(485, 179, '<font face="Courier New"><font color="#000000"><font face="Courier New, monospace"><font size="2">Trail # 179 – Snowballs of Fire!<br /><br />Hares: Certified Underwater Naval Technician, P. Ennis and the <br />wonderful twosome of Hood Whorenament and O-69.<br /><br />Visitor: Gluteus Maximus<br /><br />The moonlight off of the Bowl America in December is spectacular to <br />see!  So was the return of two long time friends (and co-founders O-<br />69 and Hood), who came out despite the weather and family <br />responsibilities to lead this rag-tag group.  Thanks guys and it is <br />always great to see you!<br /><br />So we gathered at the BA parking lot and weathered ourselves next to <br />Metro Ho for sign in and for new SH*T merchandise;  the stocking caps <br />are excellent and at $10 they\'re the &quot;In&quot; item for winter.<br /><br />While pimping more gear I noticed the return of 3 Holes No Waiting, <br />Cockspur (who was not really a returner but it didn\'t stop me), Glory <br />Hole and the elegant 14K.  We also welcomed Gluteus Max from Taiwan, <br />who was home visiting family and decided to add some SH*T to her <br />life.  <br /><br />Certified promised a simple trail for the pre-holiday events and came <br />through with grace, as trail was fun, colorful and just a bit <br />chilly.  Hares were away on time, or as close as we normally get, <br />with all Hares going in the same direction.  We commenced with the <br />usual fare before taking off to the right and into the adjoining <br />neighborhood.  <br /><br />The walkers were graced by the usually fleet footed Rodeo F*ck, who <br />decided to take it easy for a change and be FRB for the walkers.  Our <br />trail was quick and enjoyable but we never went to Certified\'s house…<br />I really wanted to see her tree, and by tree I mean….!<br /><br />We could tell that the holiday season was upon us by the kindness <br />expressed on trail by our lovely Hares (lovely does not include Hood <br />or P.Ennis), as they made sure to write, &quot;Careful Ice&quot; on the <br />walkway.  I am still not sure what constitutes careful ice.  The path <br />led us into the neighbor hood of lights and onto VA Dominion Powers\' <br />favorite holiday street.<br /><br />As done in years past, every house on the street was lit in festive <br />holiday lights and expansive decorations.  I\'d try to describe it but <br />I can\'t so deal with it.  Like last year, we came to the house with <br />Santa in the garage and the kids pouring hot chocolate for the <br />passers by.  Our intuitive 3 Holes politely asked one of the little <br />ones serving chocolate what was the special occasion for the <br />refreshments.  The little ones are so cute when you ask them an <br />obvious question.  <br /><br />We wandered the street in awe, caught up to the runners and all <br />gathered in the parking lot for a frosty beer check beverage.  <br />Reloaded and refueled we made our way back down the street and short <br />cutted back to the BA lot only to find the Sterling police and fire <br />department in full regalia in front of the establishment.<br /><br />After waiting out the authorities we saluted out FRB – Glory, FBI – <br />Puke Me Up Buttercup and DFL – Udder Ho before saying goodbye to Hood <br />and O-69.  Certified promised that the hashit was near (she only <br />lives 4 blocks away) but that she had forgotten it.  <br /><br />I\'m beginning to think I\'ll see my first born before I see that <br />hashit again!<br /><br />Violations started with Pee Wee\'s Gay House and his brilliant <br />observation that the trail was A to A; he caught on to this when Hood <br />said that a bag vehicle was unnecessary since we\'d be coming back.  <br />Whack-A-Mole and Lube Me Up Scotty spent the walk time chatting about <br />work (uhhg), Porn to Fail, Dixie Queen and Glory were late (not girl <br />late), Pimpsicle was seen kicking a Coors light box – not sure what <br />that means, and Gluteus was attempting to get someone to follow in <br />the Taiwanese tradition of pissing on the Satan Clause decorations.<br /><br />Since Watergate was in a hurry we rushed through other violations, <br />but not before Dixie warmed my heart with a personal/custom song made <br />just for me (Bob Newbanks eat your heart out).  Circle was completed <br />and a paid OnOnOn was set up in the bowling alley for one and all.  <br />That\'s about the time that Bad Dog showed up and joined the crowd for <br />a glass of milk and some munchies.  <br /><br />A good trail, some good peeps and deep fried bowling alley grub.  Now <br /></font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Symbol, serif"><font size="2">&#61514;</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Courier New, monospace"><font size="2">that\'s what I call Hashmus<br /><br />On out<br />Udder Ho</font></font></font> </font>', ''),
