(574, 326, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Trail #325, “<font color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black">The No School like the Old School trail” or alternatively, “The Revenge of the Nerds Trail”</span></font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">September 9, 2008</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Hares: Dixie Queen, The Udder Ho, Just Chris (subsequently named Three Laws of Never Getting Laid)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Made it to the hash waaayyy early with Steamer (a visitor from Dayton) and Holy F*ck in tow. Got a call in route that our brand new sign-in folks were going to be late so Holy and I decided to take over sign-in.</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">This gave us the perfect opportunity to hassle/heckle/<wbr />annoy damn near everyone in the hash.  Perfect!</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Since our new RA, The Udder Ho, was haring, our old RA, Nub, got to do Father Abraham one last time. Isn’t he lucky???  (Did I ever mention how much I HATE that song!)  We had a virgin – I can’t remember his name.  And a few visitors (I also can’t remember their names)…  Perhaps these people need to do something a little more memorable next time!  They are hashers after all – hashers should be memorable, dammit!  (Except for the virgin.  He’s not really a hasher yet – that remains to be seen if and when he comes back.)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Anyway, hares were away, circle was done and we were off.  I decided to walk and took Herpes camera with me since she was running.  I got some really blurry pictures.  But I also got two beauties!  We came across a pleasant bubbling brook and I had Nuclear Jism and Our Own Vanna re-enact the near drowning at the AGM.  Classic.  Right before we came to the little brook we met a hare (Just Chris) and he told us we were going the wrong way.  We ignored him and kept going.  What does he know?  He’s just a virgin hare.  Grow up a little and get a few more harings under your belt, Son, and then come back and tell us we’re going the wrong way.  Geez!  Other people’s children!</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">There was about 30 feet of shiggy on walkers trail as compared to about 45 minutes of field work on the runners trail.  Apparently the runners got lost.  In a field.  Doesn’t ‘field’ imply flat and open?  As in you can see all the way across?  How do you get lost in a field?  I can understand a forest where there are trees and stuff, but a field?  Seriously?  Apparently the hare had laid a rather ingenious spiraling corkscrew-type thing in the field but since the runners didn’t follow trail they came across it from a number of different directions and couldn’t figure out which was the right way.  I would have gone with a grid search like they do in CSI when looking for a body.  Of course they use the CSI version of the red shirts from Star Trek – nameless extras that could die at any moment.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Walkers got to the Beer Check without mishap (so there, Just Chris, we were going the right way!) and what did we find??!?!  Boobah the Beef Princess and some really yummy pudding shots…  Just Mary had about eight of them.  The rest of us had less.  (Mostly because she was hovering over the bowl threatening to bit off our fingers if we tried to take any of ‘her’ pudding shots.)  Screws on First decided it was time to go and the rest of us followed shortly thereafter so she wasn’t completely alone on trail.  We never did catch her and her long legs, though!</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">We got to the end, which happened to be at the top of a parking structure and waited for the runners.  And waited. And waited.  And waited.  Finally some of them came in (not on true trail) and shortly after that a truckload of runners showed up.  Lame-o’s who autohash!!!!</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">It was about this time when people began to notice other people’s hair standing on end.  At first I thought it was just one person with serious hat hair, but once we looked around it was EVERYONE!  UH-OH!!!  According to the NOAA (National Oceanic and Atmospheric Association) Preparedness Guide for Thunderstorms, Tornadoes and Lightning (<a href="http://www.nws.noaa.gov/om/brochures/ttl.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.nws.<wbr />noaa.gov/<wbr />om/brochures/<wbr />ttl.pdf</a></span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">), </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">“</span></font><font face="TimesNewRoman"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: TimesNewRoman">If you feel your skin tingle or your hair stand on end, squat low to the ground on the balls of your feet. Place your hands over your ears and your head between your knees. Make yourself the smallest target possible and minimize your contact with the ground. DO NOT lie down.” </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">I must confess that I basically gave you all up for lost and took off on my own to seek shelter leaving my bag, the hash cash and my boyfriend to fend for themselves.  I made it to the covered part of the parking structure before I turned around and at least decided to try to warn some folks.  I’m happy to say we all moved under the protected side of the parking garage and no one was struck by lightning.  It started to rain at that point anyway so we would have had to move regardless.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Once we were settled, Wookin’ Pa’ Nub opened circle.  FRB was Spikey, FBI was Just Kelly and Typical Woman and the DFLs were everyone that took a truck to the finish – lame-o autohashers!  Poonskin Cap was serenaded for her 25<sup>th</sup> analversary and was presented with a lovely bandana from her manly husband. Or was that a manly bandana from her lovely husband?  I don’t know…  ;-)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Violations:</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Typical Woman, Just Kelly and Summer’s Eve for looting street signs.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Just Mike for being a pu$$y.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Just Kyle (the virgin – now I remember his name) for acting like Mary Poppins.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Cradle to the Dreidel for going down on trail.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Nuclear Jism for his interest in golden showers.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Steamer for her advice on lubrication AND constipation on trail.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">The Udder Ho for bragging that he’s good for 45 minutes of f*cking.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Cradle to the Dreidel and Screws on First for being late to their first day on the job.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Wookin’ Pa’ Nub for being unable to get any pu$$y.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Mowgli and Buffalo Chips – the only die hards to actually do the whole trail.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">I Can’t Believe It’s Not Herpes for her wind up vibrator on trail.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Screws on First for whining.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Permanently Screwed for not being able to tie his own shoes.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Just Kyle (the virgin) for wearing two pairs of shorts.  Simultaneously.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">And How’s Her Bush and Last Week for being isolationist bastards and sitting waaayyy outside the circle.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Then we got to the naming.  </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><pre><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">“So go ahead, put us down</span></font></pre><pre><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">One of these days we will turn it around</span></font></pre><pre><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Won\'t be long, mark my words</span></font></pre><pre><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Time has come for Revenge of the nerds!”</span></font></pre><pre><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></pre><pre><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">“</span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Clap your hands everybody, and everybody clap your hands. We\'re Lambda Lambda Lambda and Omega Mu. We come here on stage tonight to do our show for you. We got a rockin’ rhythm and a hi-tech sound that\'ll make you move your body down to the ground. We got Poindexter on the violin, and Lewis and Gilbert will be joining in. We got Booger Presley on the mean guitar and a rap by little ol\' me, Lamar. We got Takashi beating on his gong, the boys and the mu\'s are clapping along. And just when you think, ya seen it all, along comes a Lambda four foot tall. So won\'t ya come on out here on the floor, so we can move our bodies, like never before…  Lammmmmmmbbbbbbbbdd<wbr />ddddaaaaaaaa”<font color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black"></span></font></span></font></pre><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">It turns out Just Chris is a nerd.  He’s in aerospace and robotics and a whole bunch of nerdy stuff.  He also likes Michigan, another strike against him.  BUT the really important thing to note here is that he is a VIRGIN!  That’s right folks.  A truly virgin hare in all sense of the word.  So…  Let the Nerd Herd get down to business!  Everyone (and I mean EVERYONE), let out their inner nerd to come up with names for Just Chris.  It was one of the better namings we’ve had in a while.  Here are the names he didn’t get (as written by The Udder Ho so don’t blame me):</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Shiver Me Dild0s</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">I Can’t Do That</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Isaac GetOff</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Space Balls</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Stephen Hawking (to be said in an electronic computer voice like Hawking uses)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Can’t Puff A Ten (I’m guessing this isn’t what was said, but I can’t read Udder’s handwriting)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Masturbation Theatre</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">How’d He Do Me</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">The Erosticator (another misspelling – Sorry Vanna)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Good Guy</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Sprocket Nerd (sp?)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lambda Lambda Lambda</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Sour’s Bitch</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Slartzy Butfest (sp?)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Poop in the Pocket</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Snatch is Not My Future</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">YankMeOff Asimov</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Don’t Panic</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">William Shatinmypants</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lift, Drag and Eject</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">C*nt on My Long Bits</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Klingons Got My …?</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Sloppy No’s</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Runner Up: A Foreskin Wrinkle in Time</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Winner: 3 Laws of Never Getting Laid</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">When asked what are the 3 laws of robotics he rattled them off without hesitation as if everyone should know them…</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Welcome to the fold, 3 Laws!</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lube Me Up Scotty</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p>', ''),
(575, 327, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Trail # 326, “<font color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black">The Adventures of Davey and Sir aka Don’t Step on the Cat and Crayfish Trail”</span></font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">September 16, 2008</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Hares: Sir Shaves A Lot, Davey Crotch Itch, Copus Interruptus</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">First thing people bitched about were the directions.  Yes, it was just an aerial photo of the start (a nondescript parking lot in Reston), but I’m sure the hares meant well.  Our oh-so-sexy webmaster at least gave you a link to the approximate spot via MSN maps (although under directions I love it that he put, “</span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">F* it. Happy searching.”).  Was this an ominous sign of things to come???</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Somehow, wankers managed to get to the start with little difficulty.  There were a couple of mishaps getting to start, most notably Herpes and Permanently Screwed, but that may have actually been a cover for some ‘alone time.’  Boinky boinky?  The Udder Ho opened circle and sent the hares on their way.  Luckily there was only one way off the parking deck that was accessible to us so we knew we wouldn’t get lost for at least the first 100 feet.  Udder then introduced the visitors and virgins at which point My C0ck Shoots Blanks had a moment with some visiting dude from Sembach in the middle of circle.  If you weren’t there, picture two sumo wrestlers coming together in an ecstatic embrace of brotherly love.  Then add beer and a kilt and you’ll get a good idea of what the circle witnessed.  We did our usual warm ups and started off on trail.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Trail led us down the stairs of the parking structure and through Reston Town Center.  That was fun!  Not just for us but for all the tourists, happy hour goers, families going out to dinner, security guards, homeless people, etc. that we ran past.  I think the security guard was more amused than pissed, but I didn’t stop to find out.  We got out of the town center and then picked up trail over near the W&amp;OD.  At this point there was a bl0w job up some stairs to the W&amp;OD just to come back down and basically jump in the creek.  We followed the creek back and forth – discovering hole and hole after hole.  (And I’m not just talking about the harriettes on trail…)  Trail led us through tick infested woods right up to the edge of the toll road.  Gets Off Easy and I actually came out on the toll road but didn’t see an ‘On Over’ so we decided we must have lost trail somewhere in the woods.  At this point, we lost trail so the trash for that part of trail goes like this:</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lost and walking</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 