(1114, 578, '<div>The hash descended upon Green Briar Park in what\'s listed as Fairfax</div><div>but is a stones throw from Chantilly High School. The weather</div><div>threatened to get pretty bad but it never really amounted to much</div><div>during trail or circle... but it was a verified flash flood once we</div><div>got to the Blue Iguana!</div><div><br /></div><div>The Theme was Siete de Mayo, and my Mexican alter-ego (Eleccion de</div><div>Catadores) met runners at start in traditional sombrero and sarape</div><div>(from the traditional party store.) It was explained to the walkers</div><div>and runners that they would both be enjoying Mexican themed Beer and</div><div>Shot Checks and off the walkers hares Vaginger Monolouges and Little</div><div>Cock that Wont went. I had neglected to get any of my hare gear ready</div><div>so I had to grab my flour and set my timer but then was off... only to</div><div>be seen by the pack a few minutes later as I tried to sneak behind the</div><div>baseball field.. oh well as they say. The best laid plans... never</div><div>happen!</div><div><br /></div><div>The following is from accounts of trail recounted later by the pack (4</div><div>runners, 2 walkers). Becuz He Can stayed true to trail and followed my</div><div>On-Out marks left even though he knew it would veer off to the right</div><div>behind and around the baseball field.... Doctor Strangelove, Fudd</div><div>Mucker, and Bad Dog decided to shortcut over walkers trail.... lazy</div><div>wankers still never came close to catching me!</div><div>Off into Big Rocky Run Stream Valley Park, and out into the labyrinth</div><div>that is Fairfax County suburbs, twisting through the streets and their</div><div>neatly manicured lawns before splitting off from the walkers and</div><div>heading to a back check down hill through the thorn laced Virginia</div><div>Power Line Easement. The pack found a check on Fair Lakes Parkway and</div><div>at this point Fudd Mucker apparently decided to take the Mexican theme</div><div>to the max and headed south with no sign of flour until he saw Guapos.</div><div>The pack winded through another town home complex and around Northrop</div><div>Grummans private retention pond into the beer check, complete with a</div><div>mural of female genitalia by a local \'Urban-Artist&amp;#39;. The hash had</div><div>their choice of Tecate, Sol, Modelo Especial, Corona Extra, Dos Equis,</div><div>Bud-Light Strawberry-Rita, and a special Mexican treat of Bud Light &amp;</div><div>Clamato Chelada Style! (more on that later) Bad Dog skipped the Beer</div><div>Check and headed off as FRB and blew threw a Walker\'s-Runners Split</div><div>choosing the walker\'s side. The Runner\'s headed down the power line</div><div>easement towards the Fairfax County Parkway (arguably they headed Up</div><div>and Down as this portion of the trail was pretty hilly!) A Back Check</div><div>at the end of the easement slowed the now 3 runners down a bit before</div><div>they headed north back into the neighborhoods and winding back toward</div><div>the Park. Meanwhile, Bad Dog was meandering around a neighborhood</div><div>following parts of Walker\'s Trail before the Walkers catch up and say</div><div>&quot;Hey, The Runner\'s went back down the Easement&quot;. So off he followed,</div><div>getting lost at the back check and then running back into the walkers</div><div>quite some time later. The Runners wove in and out of the park and</div><div>took a dip in Big Rocky Run (whose current was beefed up a little</div><div>following the previous 24 hours of rain!) en route to the Shot Check.</div><div>They were treated to some pre-mixed Margarita, and flasks of Silver</div><div>Tequila, and Gold Tequila! Thinking the walkers had already hit the</div><div>check, they took the shots with them and proceeded back out into</div><div>civilization and then... you guessed it, back into the park! The</div><div>aforementioned walkers were wandering aimlessly around in an 0.25km</div><div>squared area trying to figure out whatever Vaginger and Little Cock</div><div>laid for them. The runners came to a Runners Walkers split that was</div><div>meant to take them across the run again, but they were weak and said</div><div>no thanks, following Walkers trail back in... and missing the</div><div>shiggiest part of trail right near the end of Runner\'s True Trail. Oh</div><div>well, at least I had fun setting it! On their way in they ran into</div><div>Little Cock who had gone out to find the Walkers and passed off the</div><div>Shot Check to him (why they didn\'t keep at least one bottle I don\'t</div><div>know!) Finally Bad Dog led in the walkers and we all sat around</div><div>enjoying tales of the previous hours hi-jinks.</div><div><br /></div><div>Bad Dog, having missed the Beer Check and apparently never having</div><div>heard of the beverage, quickly fell in love with the Chelada Style</div><div>beer with Clam juice. Repeatedly expressing his joy at the discovery</div><div>and offering to do down-downs with it. I re-donned my Sombrero and</div><div>Sarape and Udder kicked off our circle (which he had lost control of</div><div>before it even started) When asked for a song for welcoming our Justs</div><div>into the circle, I improvised and came up with a song I shall now call</div><div>&quot;the circle song&quot;... it goes like this (with a planar clarification</div><div>added by Dr Strangelove) &quot;A Circle is the set of all points (on a</div><div>plane) equidistant from a central point.... yeeeeah Circle!&quot;.... Udder</div><div>said \'What was that?&quot; and I replied &quot;Euclidean definition!&quot;. Don\'t ask</div><div>what melody I sang, that was also impromptu! Fudd Mucker gave the</div><div>hares a compliment (I think)... It wasn\'t a bad trail... but it wasnt</div><div>good either. I told him he\'s more than welcome to set one himself to</div><div>show us better :)</div><div><br /></div><div>Circle details:</div><div><br /></div><div>Justs-</div><div>The Dynamic Duo - Just Audrey and Just Adrian.... Why again did we let</div><div>two justs go off by themselves on walker\'s trail? It\'s no wonder they</div><div>got lost! Just Audrey was a huge fan of the BudLight Strawberry-Rita,</div><div>grabbing the rest of the case and downing as much as Just Adrian would</div><div>let her.</div><div><br /></div><div>Violations-</div><div>Taster\'s Choice: For trying to impersonate Sasquatch as he tried</div><div>sneaking by in the sight of the pack so they wouldnt see where true</div><div>trail was from start, after having just spent the previous 3 minutes</div><div>laying a check in the opposite direction. I swear I thought they</div><div>couldnt see me on the other side of the baseball field against the</div><div>treeline in my red long sleeve shirt!</div><div>Becuz He Can: For being the only runner that actually followed the</div><div>true trail Taster\'s laid, while the rest of the pack shortcutted to</div><div>the scene of the BigFoot Sighting.</div><div>Vaginger Monolouges and Little Cock: For being too cheap to pay hash</div><div>Cash and haring two weeks in a row (I appreciate the help greatly</div><div>though!)</div><div>Bad Dog: For being DFL and FRB... last runner in but lead the walkers in!</div><div>I\'m sure there were some others, but I forgot.</div><div><br /></div><div>After Swing Low, we started cleaning up when a nice Policeman drove</div><div>by, shining his light on Bad Dog. (as the hare ditched his sombrero</div><div>and sarape as not to look suspicious)</div><div>&quot;Is that a beer you have there?&quot; the officer asked,</div><div>to which Bad Dog replied &quot;Nope just a Fresca!&quot;</div><div>and off the officer drove into the night to worry about other things.</div><div><br /></div><div>The pack followed Taster\'s Choice to the On-After, but Vaginger</div><div>Monolouges sped ahead and took the pole position (tee hee hee), but</div><div>managed to take a wrong turn and forced a full pack U-Turn in the</div><div>Jason\'s Deli Parking lot. We finally found our way to the Blue</div><div>Iguana, and proceeded to enjoy the beer and food available. I was only</div><div>able to stay for 20 mins but did enjoy my Blue Cheese Burger! On-on to</div><div>next week with Strokin\' My Wife Away!</div><div><br /></div><div>-Taster\'s Choice</div>', ''),
