(1216, 597, '&nbsp;So Happy It\'s Tuesday Hash House Harriers Trail #596<div><br></div><div>"National Felt Hats Day" Trail</div><div><br></div><div>Hares: Strokin\' my Wife Away and Parent\'s Weekend</div><div><br></div><div>Location: FFX Federal Credit Union parking lot off of 29</div><div><br></div><div>On-on-on: Chili\'sâ€¦. no John\'s Placeâ€¦ no Chili\'sâ€¦.. damnit.. how about</div><div>Primetime Grill? Shot-girls... yes please!</div><div><br></div><div>The Pack:</div><div>AndHowsHerBush, The Udder Ho, Silver Lining, Taster\'s Choice, Iowa,</div><div>Mark Twaint, All The Way In, FudMucker, The Otter Pink Meat, The</div><div>Vaginger Monolouges, Horse Jerker, Little Cock That Won\'t, Dr</div><div>Strangelove, SWATT</div><div><br></div><div>Justs: (Naming details below!)</div><div>Just Christian, Just Patrick</div><div><br></div><div>Greetings fellow Shitters, for those that don\'t recall: This is a Hash</div><div>Trash. The purposes of â€œthe trashâ€ are many:</div><div><br></div><div>A) to chronicle for the ages our nefarious deeds</div><div><br></div><div>B) to remind those in attendance what we did (I can\'t think of any</div><div>reason you might forget!)</div><div><br></div><div>C) to make those who didn\'t join us see what they missed and encourage</div><div>them to join the next week</div><div><br></div><div>D) to give the trash author some brief validation of his</div><div>self-described wittiness as he giggles to himself while writing it.</div><div><br></div><div>I challenge you all to try your hand at it every now and then</div><div>(especially next weekâ€¦ cause I won\'t be there)</div><div><br></div><div>And so it began....</div><div>The intrepid hashers of SH!T gathered on this fine Tuesday evening in</div><div>the back parking lot of FFXFCU in anticipation of another Tuesday</div><div>night\'s misguided adventures through the lands west of the beltway.</div><div>The majority of the hash pulled their vehicles into the oversized</div><div>diagonal parking spaces, anticipating their inability to pull out</div><div>later without causing damage to adjacent cars. The Beermeister arrived</div><div>prior to trail to the vocal excitement of the pack who last week tried</div><div>to chase him down .25 miles into trail!</div><div><br></div><div>In keeping with the tradition of every trail having some theme or</div><div>dedication (no matter how far out of left field it is pulled) this</div><div>week\'s trail celebrated â€œNational Felt Hat Day.â€ The Hairs donned</div><div>something felt, I can\'t recall. Silver Lining sported a dashing</div><div>wizard-type cone hat, Vaginger went all Yule-tide with a Santa hat</div><div>(that had some shedding issues). I myself donned a large Lobster hat</div><div>(held on with my newly acquired 25 Run Bandana!) There were a few</div><div>others, but I can\'t recall (Note to self, start making notes before</div><div>trail starts, and not just halfway through circle!) With nor Virgins</div><div>we didn\'t need chalk-talk but that didn\'t stop us from drawing a</div><div>chalk-outline of Silver Lining laying on the ground.... which then</div><div>morphed into an abstract childlike turtle drawing... which was in no</div><div>way a depiction of Silver\'s usual trail speed!</div><div><br></div><div>We half-heartedly blessed the Hares and sent them on their way, before</div><div>starting up our usual half-hearted chorus of Father Abraham (Does</div><div>anyone know why we sing that? I understand the mock-stretchingâ€¦. But</div><div>was curious as to maybe if it\'s a ploy to seem as some religious group</div><div>in the event of interruption by â€œauthoritiesâ€) After an extended</div><div>period to give the Hare\'s a head start (With these two FRB\'s haring,</div><div>did they really need it?) we lumbered off south into a subdivision</div><div>before circling a retention pond and bounding into the north end of</div><div>Fair Villa Park. My plan this week was to take it easy due to some</div><div>knee issuesâ€¦ but I guess I\'m a glutton for punishment and found myself</div><div>in with the FRB\'s for most of trail. The hares provided us with a</div><div>trail of flour and multiple deep checks over and around the trails of</div><div>the park, leading us south as the sun set and left us plodding through</div><div>the dark (especially Doc Strangelove). After approx.. 1.75 miles we</div><div>found the BC hidden at a small grove of bamboo. Some hasher\'s may</div><div>remember this location from the amazing trail #556 set last December</div><div>by Stab My Cock and me. This was the place where (the slower section</div><div>of) the pack was approached by an angry homeowner with a Cross bow who</div><div>didn\'t appreciate our cries of â€˜On-On\' and â€˜Are You?\'. I believe it</div><div>was Erectional Officer that mouthed off to him and then Lush of the</div><div>Irish and Little Cock who were left then to handle FFX County\'s finest</div><div>who came to the sceneâ€¦ anyways! After the runner\'s downed a few cold</div><div>ones over horror stories of SWATT\'s online dating experiences, some</div><div>decided to follow a Runner\'s Walker\'s split up Andes Dr into a</div><div>neighborhood. Always one to choose shaggy over pavement, myself and</div><div>the rest bounded into wooded George Mason Univ property with a maze of</div><div>trails that snaked us over a mile into a GMU Parking lot and back up</div><div>into civilization again. We snaked through the darkened streets of</div><div>residential Fairfax, and tramped across the campus of Fairfax Villa</div><div>Elementary in a loop that cost us half a mile we\'ll never get back.</div><div>The remainder of trail led us in a winding manner northwest back</div><div>towards the start and connecting us back to the walker\'s trailâ€¦. For</div><div>about two miles! As the lights of the commercial enterprises on 29 lit</div><div>the horizon we knew we were back towards the beginning. The pack gave</div><div>â€˜Buenas Noches\' greetings to the Residentes of Los trailer park we</div><div>traversed and then curved back around the Credit Union to see the</div><div>smiling Hare\'s awaiting our return. I recorded approx. 5.25 miles,</div><div>however I also checked the wrong way significantly more times than</div><div>right. All The Way In, seemed to have the ability to smell the hares</div><div>and was without question the one to be following at checks this</div><div>evening!</div><div><br></div><div>Somehow the runners who gave up after the beer check, managed to get</div><div>lost in what should have been a cut-and-dry shortcut back to runner\'s</div><div>trail and got lost out in the mean streets of FFX. Seriously? In this</div><div>area you can\'t ever go too far without hitting a major street!</div><div>Members of the pack decided to venture out to scout them down, with</div><div>Just Christian leading the chivalrous charge just in time for the</div><div>walkers to round the corner and head in. Later AndHowsHer arrived in</div><div>with word that John\'s Place looked dark? (Waitâ€¦. Trail went nowhere</div><div>near John\'s Place!) He had managed to go almost 2 miles out of his way</div><div>to the 29/50 split and worked his way back to start! Eventually</div><div>everyone made it in and we kicked off Circle.</div><div><br></div><div>We had no Virgins this week but plenty of returnersâ€¦. Who I didn\'t</div><div>write down. But they drank.</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Just Christian</div><div><br></div><div>FBI: SWATT</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div><br></div><div>All The Way In- Something about small holes and losing his True Trail</div><div>signsâ€¦. I should have started taking notes quickerâ€¦. It was the first</div><div>violation, if you want better detail then write your own trash!</div><div><br></div><div>Doc Strangelove â€“ For too little too late! He had a dysfunctional</div><div>headlamp until we finished trail. That\'s like getting an erection</div><div>after your partner has already left the bedroom!</div><div><br></div><div>Lush of the Irish â€“ Marking the start location as her territory.</div><div>After complaining about the lack of bathroom facilities at start and</div><div>finishâ€¦. She used the same tree both times as a substitute so any</div><div>other folks would know that is her spot.</div><div><br></div><div>Just Christian â€“ Rudeness to walker\'s he won\'t be going home with. He</div><div>ignored the rest of the Walkers as they came in, only asking how Otter</div><div>was.</div><div><br></div><div>SWATTT- Not having priorities straight! She was overhead describing</div><div>how she turned down a free offer of massage, oils, and worst of all a</div><div>case of beer from a potential suitor!</div><div><br></div><div>Strokin â€“ For taking the trail through a local rape-camp (a term I was</div><div>not aware of until circle) that had a bizarre Deliverance vibe mixed</div><div>with some good old fashioned patriotism in the form of a weathered US</div><div>Flagâ€¦. (when one hare drinks!) Some questioned if the two fast hares</div><div>had a quick rendezvous here during the setting of trailâ€¦</div><div><br></div><div>HASHIT!</div><div><br></div><div>Last week\'s recipient, AndHowsHerBush, did his best Dickens-esque</div><div>Jacob Marley impression on trail this week as he rattled the HASHIT</div><div>adorned with chains of empty beer cans.</div><div><br></div><div>Suggestions for this week\'s winner included:</div><div><br></div><div>Lush â€“ for leaving her keys in Little Cock\'s Ass (like a stopwatch in</div><div>Pulp Fiction)</div><div><br></div><div>____ - for purchasing last minute running clothes from Sears before</div><div>trail and leaving the tags on so he could return them after. (Note: do</div><div>not wear clothes from Sear\'s without washing them first!)</div><div><br></div><div>Iowa/Mark Twaint â€“ for getting married this coming weekend and then</div><div>leaving us to go on an extended honeymoon and not having the decency</div><div>to at least invite us along and lay a trail.</div><div><br></div><div>Vaginger/Monolouges â€“ Either for having sex on trail last week or NOT</div><div>having sex on trail this weekâ€¦ you pick. Pictures or it didn\'t happen!</div><div><br></div><div>And the winner wasâ€¦.. I don\'t knowâ€¦ I forgot to mark it down. Show up</div><div>next Tuesday and see who has it! (for some reason I think the</div><div>newlyweds were getting it)</div><div><br></div><div>We then proceeded to have a tandem naming!</div><div><br></div><div>Just Christian: is involved with The Otter Pink Meat (just a few years</div><div>his junior), is a Soldier who has been an Airborne Ranger but now</div><div>serves as a Data ANALyst. He enjoys cake in the same manner as a</div><div>fat-kid, is a racist (of the road variety, not socially), has a pair</div><div>of teenage daughters, has a fetish for mathematics, keeps dogs usually</div><div>reserved for Kardashian and Hilton heiresses (a Pughuahua?), once had</div><div>sex on a seawall in Jamaica, finds himself disturbingly attracted to</div><div>Janice the Muppet, and has an unhealthy obsession with Britney Bitch.</div><div><br></div><div>Suggestions included: Have your Cake and Eat it, Dutch Oven, Captain</div><div>CockCakes, Shit Me Baby One More Time, Shit Me Spears, and Flaccid</div><div>Rancid Boner (FRB)</div><div><br></div><div>Just Patrick: is involved with Vaginger, is a Utilities Marker, once</div><div>had sex with a girl who had not removed her used feminine hygiene</div><div>products from her person, recently had sex on the Clifton Railroad,</div><div>likes hash brownies, used to work as Best Buy (at the same time as</div><div>Vaginger, but pre-relationship.</div><div><br></div><div>Suggestions included: Pecker, The Rescuer Down Under, Forgot One in</div><div>the Oven, Miss Utility, Laying Track, Questionable Utility. Miss</div><div>Uturdity, Tampon Rescue.</div><div><br></div><div>After much deliberationâ€¦â€¦â€¦ for now and forever more in the world of</div><div>hashing (blah blah Blah) these two wankers will be known as</div><div>(Respectively)</div><div><br></div><div>Mathterbates and Track Marks!</div><div><br></div><div>Following the naming, we wished Iowa and Mark Twaint the best as they</div><div>have their nuptials this weekend and abandon us to tramp across the</div><div>globe, and of course the best of luck as they have sex for the first</div><div>time! (wink, wink, nudge, nudge) A little round of â€˜Swing Low\' and we</div><div>argued about where to go next. It was decided to try John\'s Place and</div><div>if it was closed (which it was) venture to Chili\'sâ€¦. which had 5</div><div>minutes left of kitchen time but had already given last â€“callâ€¦ kind of</div><div>a serious hash deal breaker. So we moved on to Primetime Grill!</div><div><br></div><div>We were welcomed by the Ciroc Girls who were doing promotional shots</div><div>for anyone who wanted. #winning. Those who joined us sampled some</div><div>beers and ordered some chow. Mental Note: I owe Mathterbates a few</div><div>beers after downing his once accidentally and another time with</div><div>intent!</div><div><br></div><div>Off I went into the night so I have no more to pass on regarding</div><div>further hash shenanigans at Primetime, but with some sort of</div><div>all-you-can drink deal they had going I can only assume it got crazy.</div><div>Hope to see you on trail again soon, and look forward to hearing what</div><div>adventures occur during and after next week\'s trail!</div><div><br></div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div>', ''),
