(1218, 602, '<div>So Happy It\'s Tuesday Hash Run #601</div><div>October 15, 2013 - Fairfax, VA</div><div>The Hares:</div><div>Parent\'s Weekend</div><div>Just Joe</div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div><div><br></div><div>All together, 18 Wankers and 2 T.U.R.D.s (Tethered Urban Running Dogs)</div><div>enjoyed the trail!</div><div><br></div><div>The Pack:</div><div>ATWI</div><div>Udder Ho</div><div>Vaginger Monolouges</div><div>Herpicles</div><div>SWWAT</div><div>Strokin\' my Wife Away</div><div>The Otter Pink Meat</div><div>I\'m Falling and I Can\'t Get it Up</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>Read Between the Slime</div><div>Fudd Mucker</div><div>Cheese Jizz</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>Dildo</div><div>Just Finley</div><div><br></div><div>Visitors/Virgins:</div><div>Burning Bubbles â€“ first time visitor from C2H5OH (Columbus â€œCowtown</div><div>with a Hard-onâ€ Hash House Harriers &amp; Harriettes, OH)</div><div>Just Allen â€“ Virgin</div><div><br></div><div>Be Warned: Trash comes from the viewpoint of one of the haresâ€¦ and the</div><div>Walker\'s Hare at thatâ€¦ but you don\'t really expect truth from these</div><div>anyway do you?</div><div><br></div><div>It was just your average low 70s mid-October day in Fairfax, VA as the</div><div>pack assembled in the back lot of the Fairfax Towne Center. (Except</div><div>Vaginger, who tried to assemble in the parking lot of the nearby</div><div>Fairfax Commons and had to call and ask where we all were) There was</div><div>initial alarm as a FFX County Firefighters HazMat truck pulled up</div><div>alongside the packâ€¦. but any fear subsided as they unloaded and headed</div><div>into the shopping center to grab chow. Whew, crisis averted! All The</div><div>Way In set up the Haberdashery from the tailgate of his truck like he</div><div>was hawking wolf-pack/full-moon-shirts and snow-globes at a flea</div><div>market. Even attracting a non-hasher who was returning from watching a</div><div>movie with his wife and was curious as to what was being sold! That\'s</div><div>right, the HAB was available, BRING YOUR EXTRA CASH and grab some swag</div><div>at the next hash!</div><div><br></div><div>The sizable fall/winter pack mingled in the fairly open and public</div><div>spot for a while before sending the Hare\'s off. This was to be Just</div><div>Joe\'s virgin hare experienceâ€¦. So why did we let Parent\'s Weekend and</div><div>myself take him out alone, we obviously can\'t teach him anything!</div><div>Either way, the young padowan was eager to ingest all the finer points</div><div>of hare-dom from us as we ran off into the distance. The remainder of</div><div>the trail description may or may not be what actually occurred for the</div><div>pack.... I can only vouch for the part of trail leading up to the beer</div><div>check and then the walker\'s split!</div><div><br></div><div>The pack left start and made their way into a nearby townhome</div><div>neighborhood skirting Highway 50 before arriving at a check that was</div><div>solved behind a fence and into the back parking structure of the</div><div>building housing the International Association of Fire Chiefs, I hope</div><div>they enjoyed the mysterious white splotches when they came to work the</div><div>next day! another check and trail was found on a paved path heading</div><div>west and down into Fair Ridge Park, past some nefarious people</div><div>conducting business on a tennis court in the dark. After a few checks</div><div>to slow the pack down they ran alongside some condos into a back check</div><div>that went straight into some deep dark and wet shiggy... if you made</div><div>it out of there without a scratch, then you have my admiration! I</div><div>threw my socks away when I got home because I didn\'t even want to</div><div>start picking out all the burs that gotten attached. Some of our more</div><div>balance-challenged hashers (Cough cough Silver Linings Cough Cough)</div><div>had difficulty staying vertical and tried doing flips into the muddy</div><div>drainage area before trail led back up onto a trail and down towards</div><div>and around a large retention pond. Always looking to get a few extra</div><div>seconds ahead of the pack the hares dropped another back Check along</div><div>the FFX County Parkway and the pack retraced their steps along the</div><div>pond before heading up the hill and heading down the parkway in the</div><div>other direction. A split showed the pack to head down into a drainage</div><div>tunnel for their first frosty on-trail treats. The Hares were nice</div><div>enough to leave a Boob Check just after... I never did find out if</div><div>that got solved properly! Walkers shot back out onto Monument drive</div><div>and headed back East towards the start, but the Runners continued off</div><div>into Rocky Run Park to enjoy a shot check, and down along a Power</div><div>Easement before finding another tunnel (Thanks ATWI for picking up</div><div>Just Finley on the rocky hill at the tunnel exit, the tunnel was a</div><div>spur of the moment addition by the Runners Hares!) Trail continued in</div><div>an around the neighborhoods of Ox Hill and pushed through the historic</div><div>Civil War battle monument and back in towards start.....</div><div><br></div><div>Now that\'s how it was supposed to go..... As Walker\'s Hare I passed</div><div>the runner pack as they were heading into beer check. I had been</div><div>slowed down by the other hares who found some trail treasure in the</div><div>form of a 2\' long and fairly wide PVC pipe that they wanted me to take</div><div>back to start for use as a Safety Third device... Sure thing I said as</div><div>I ran through the tunnel to pick it up where they left it. I should</div><div>have just said "Screw it!" that thing was bulky and a pain in the ass</div><div>to carry as I ran down the street attempting to lay walker\'s trail. I</div><div>must have tried 10 different methods of carrying that cursed thing</div><div>before I finally just held it across the yoke of my shoulders, many a</div><div>strange look was given by local pedestrians... and I was probably</div><div>audibly cursing too, that didn\'t help.</div><div><br></div><div>Sooo, I got back and waited.... and waited.... and waited.. and then</div><div>at about 8:30 PM I heard an On-On! Yeah, finally some people to talk</div><div>too and not just folks returning from their shopping and staring at me</div><div>in my Kilt and Tuxedo shirt... The Walker\'s headed in and I knew the</div><div>second half of Runner\'s must have had some issues! We continued to</div><div>wait and it wasn\'t until another 15 minutes that the Runners started</div><div>to trickle in! The Hares beat them in just barely and said the pack</div><div>had been on their heels for a bit. Either way, we set up shop smack</div><div>dab in the corner or the parking lot and dared anyone to keep us from</div><div>having our circle.... luckily no one tried!</div><div><br></div><div>Returners:</div><div>- Cheez-Jizz</div><div>- FuddMucker</div><div><br></div><div>No Analverseries because we don\'t have the data with us!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: I\'ve Fallen and I Can\'t Get it Up (and he came in limping at that!)</div><div>FWB: Udder Ho</div><div>FBI: Burning Bubbles</div><div>FWBI: Vaginger Monolouges</div><div>DFL: Strokin\' my Wife Away</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div>- SWWAT wants a Wacky Wavy Arm-Flailing Inflatable Tube Man, when</div><div>there is plenty of the live variety standing around the circle!</div><div>- The Otter Pink Meat apparently doesn\'t know what paper money is and</div><div>paid for Hash Cash in Quarters (Note, Vaginger hates this... we should</div><div>all do it)</div><div>- Parent\'s Weekend for touching Just Joe\'s tip while â€œLayingâ€ trail.</div><div>- Silver Lining - For trying to do Gymnastics on trail and almost</div><div>drowning in a puddle.</div><div>- Just Finley â€“ for crotch punching males and females (It\'s just how</div><div>he says I love you !)</div><div>- Read Between The Slime â€“ for not having a headlamp while going</div><div>through dark wet tunnels! Gotta have protection!</div><div>- Udder Ho â€“ for Hash-Hypocrisy, violating Read Between The Slime for</div><div>not having a headlamp on trail when he himself DID NOT have a headlamp</div><div>on trail!</div><div>- Silver Lining â€“ Forgot to get Ice so the beer was not at it\'s</div><div>coldest for circle. Yummy, luke warm Light Beer!</div><div>- Burning Bubbles â€“ for doing a Dorothy Gale impression (sans pigtails</div><div>and gingham dressâ€¦ that would have been nice) and wearing some</div><div>blinged-up shiny-ass shoes (Ruby Slippers) into circle.</div><div>- Haresâ€¦ for what elseâ€¦ a SHITTY Trail!</div><div><br></div><div>Our virgin, Just Allen, was brought into the circle and The Otter Pink</div><div>Meat helped show him the proper form for doing a down-down (with the</div><div>newâ€¦. And already brokenâ€¦ Hash-Shit!) Hopefully the sight of a</div><div>hyperactive harriette with Dildo in tow gulping down her favorite</div><div>beverage of choice from a TikiTorch didn\'t scare</div><div><br></div><div>Time to pass on the Hash-Shit came and Otter had to be reminded that</div><div>she is afforded the opportunity to nominate someone else! All The Way</div><div>In was nominated for some half-assed reason but the pack was unanimous</div><div>in voting for The Otter Pink Meat again as she had managed to break</div><div>the damn thing in it\'s first week of use!!! I think she likes the</div><div>thing, but said it has difficulty fitting in her trunk!</div><div><br></div><div>We sang our favorite hymn and headed on out, but not before I lost my</div><div>iPhone trying to get Just Finley to pee one last time.... I knew it</div><div>couldn\'t be far because I had just used it, but after about 10 minutes</div><div>of tearing apart my car and slowly policing the area it was found!</div><div>All in all, a great run with a fun bunch on a gorgeous night.</div><div><br></div><div>Just Joe has hared now so you know what that means! Start thinking up</div><div>stories and possible names Wankers!</div><div><br></div><div>Come join us tomorrow as BadDog completes has the second day of his</div><div>SexFecta Trail Series celebrating various Analversaries at the DC area</div><div>Hashes, or as I\'m referring to it......</div><div><br></div><div>TOUR D\'UH LOST</div><div><br></div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div>', ''),
