(1226, 606, '<div>The Loosen Up Trail</div><div>Trail #605: Reston, VA</div><div>November 12, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>This week’s Trail was titled “the Loosen Up” Trail because it was</div><div>national Loosen up day or some shit like that. The Hare’s took it</div><div>literally and thought it meant loosen up your legs… by running 6 miles</div><div>in the freezing cold.</div><div><br></div><div>Location:</div><div>Reston South Park &amp; Ride Lot</div><div><br></div><div>Hares:</div><div>Strokin\' My Wife Away, Taster\'s Choice</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Parents Weekend</div><div>The Otter Pink Meat</div><div>The Vaginger Monolouges</div><div>I’ve Fallen and I Can’t Get it Up</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>FuddMucker</div><div>Because He Can</div><div>Whack and Spurt</div><div>Holy Fuck</div><div>Bad Dog (possibly still on trail)</div><div>Just Allen</div><div><br></div><div>TURDs: (Tethered Urban Running Dog):</div><div>Koda</div><div>Dildo</div><div><br></div><div>Generally as the weather turns colder, Hares will shorten trails. Well</div><div>not this week. Strokin’ and I didn’t even give the pack a warning as</div><div>to how far we would be going as we bounded off into the Park nestled</div><div>between Lawyer Road and Glade Drive in Reston. The Pack huddled</div><div>together trying to keep warm as the time to chase after the Hares</div><div>approached. We had a drive-by by Swing and Whiff who wanted to say hi</div><div>and check out any new Hab we were offering, of course ATWI was happy</div><div>to oblige.</div><div><br></div><div>As the pack took off, they headed straight into the woods and soon</div><div>came across toilet paper strewn on tree branches…. It is a good thing</div><div>it was a smart pack tonight because the hares had forgotten to mention</div><div>any use of TP to mark trail. After a brief wooded excursion, trail</div><div>began following some of Reston’s beautiful paved walkways, however</div><div>with the extreme winds recently they were mostly covered with leaves.</div><div>A few checks helped slow the pack down and the trail went through a</div><div>delightful tunnel underneath Steeplechase Road. The Hares hoped to buy</div><div>ourselves a few more minutes of lead time with an artfully crafted</div><div>Back-Check up Steeplechase, but I’m pretty sure it only slowed down</div><div>ATWI by a few seconds. Shortly after the back check, a split for</div><div>runners and walkers took the runner’s east onto a wooded trail and the</div><div>walkers across a footbridge north. Walker’s opted for a few hundred</div><div>yards towards the beer-check (and didn’t find it) while the runner’s</div><div>had no clue they were embarking on a 3 mile loop! The runner’s</div><div>proceeded along trail in and out of the woods but generally heading</div><div>the same direction. I left a few checks (and one back check up a hill</div><div>that actually slowed them down this time!) along the path but it</div><div>generally kept going straight for about one and half a miles. When you</div><div>know the FRBs are faster than you (and you are bogged down with lbs of</div><div>flour) every check helps! I happened upon a great little fire pit</div><div>near Soapstone Dr and dropped off the first Shot Check to help warm up</div><div>the pack, Pink Electric Lemonade! Trail continued underneath Soapstone</div><div>through a tunnel that (unknown to the Hare who can’t smell) contained</div><div>some pretty hideous sludge and quite possibly sewage…. If I had known</div><div>this when I was running through it I would have enjoyed it more, but</div><div>at least I got a laugh at finish as the runner’s complained that I</div><div>didn’t have the decency to take them through a clean creek later to</div><div>wash off the stench! Trail finally turned in a different direction</div><div>crossing the creek by bridge and turning 180 at a playground. Off the</div><div>runner’s went for half a mile down an unpaved wooded path. I then took</div><div>them north and uphill before winding down into a small ravine for</div><div>another delicious shot to help them forget that they had ran 3.25</div><div>miles already and were still no closer than 2 miles to start (as the</div><div>crow flies). A little Peach Tea with Schnapps apparently did the trick</div><div>and off they went up to Glade Road. The pavement pounding was short</div><div>lived as right after crossing Soapstone they dove back into the trails</div><div>and continued on for just under a mile before coming across the first</div><div>TRUE TRAIL ALL of the night. At this point I ducked back to start</div><div>while the trail continued to a beer check just through the woods….</div><div>Unless you were the walkers who demanded that they saw a Check-8 and</div><div>not a B-Check… I actually believed them until the runners came back</div><div>and insisted that Strokin’ left a B-Check! The last mile or so of</div><div>trail worked its way through the woods and past Strokin’s Boyhood home</div><div>(who knows what things he used to do in these woods!?) before arcing</div><div>back to start where ice-cold beverages and orange food awaited!</div><div>Parents Weekend noted that it was a great trail…. For JULY! Would you</div><div>like some Cheese (balls) with your whine! Just think of it this way,</div><div>by running so far you kept warm longer in this freezing ass weather!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Just Allen (he really likes to “win” the hash)</div><div>FBI: The Otter Pink Meat</div><div>DFL: Did Bad Dog ever make it in?</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div>Otter – PETA Alert, Thinking she was on Project Runway and wearing her</div><div>dogs as some sort of living boa. However on an unrelated note… I came</div><div>across this website and thought she might like it.</div><div>http://www.buzzfeed.com/chelseamarshall/the-happiest-otters-of-all-time</div><div>Bad Dog – (In absentia) before trail he chided the Hares for not</div><div>having a working Port-a-Potty at start (is that a serious expectation</div><div>at hash anyway?!), insisting that it was locked (it wasn’t)… but never</div><div>actually tried to open it. I’ve Fallen stood in as the Stunt-Dog.</div><div>Just Allen – Thought it was Halloween still, dressed up in a Spider</div><div>Man Shirt and came skipping into Finish clutching the leftover shot</div><div>check bag like it was his Trick-or-treat Candy Bag!</div><div>Tasters Choice – for giving the pack a disturbing mental image of Bad</div><div>Dog keeping himself company on trail with his Sock-Puppet gloves.</div><div>Otter and All The Way In – Shared sex toys on trail, All The Way In</div><div>picked up Otter’s Dildo partway through trail and ran with him.</div><div><br></div><div>It was cold so we didn’t spend too much time in circle. I mean really</div><div>fricking cold… my dumbass couldn’t find gloves until I got home and</div><div>realized they were underneath the wet clothes I had changed out of! I</div><div>can barely read the notes I took at circle cause my handwriting was so</div><div>shaky. However the cold didn’t stop All The Way In from hawking the</div><div>brand new hot off the presses Day-Glo/Night-Glo SoHappy shirts….</div><div>Vaginger modeled the first one out of the box and, with the help of</div><div>the chilly air, provided her own headlights to show off the reflective</div><div>nature of the shirt!</div><div><br></div><div>HASHSHIT:</div><div>Vaginger was kind enough to add a new cup to the hashshit (be careful</div><div>drinking out of it, it has got a sharp edge!) as well as a cigarette</div><div>holder to keep your smokes handy while on trail. She kindly nominated</div><div>Strokin’ My Wife Away for drawing a B that looked like an 8 and thus</div><div>confusing the walkers (but not the runners?). Udder nominated I’ve</div><div>Fallen who keeps hurting himself yet not allowing his body to heal.</div><div>You have to admire the tenacity of a hasher that just won’t let things</div><div>like physical pain and possible permanent damage get in the way of</div><div>chasing hares! It was a close one but Strokin’ won it for the week!</div><div><br></div><div>Bad-Dog was still out there but we decided to move on to warmer</div><div>locales by hitting up Glory Days… I thought Parents and I were going</div><div>to go, but we had a miscommunication as we got in the car. After about</div><div>5 minutes of driving I asked him… “How far away is this Bar?”… “Oh, I</div><div>didn’t think we were going” oh well, I opted for Taco Bell instead as</div><div>we headed on home. Maybe one of you wankers can fill us in on the</div><div>Glory Days shenanigans? On a similar note, I won’t be on trail next</div><div>week so I challenge someone else to try their hand at writing a trash</div><div>to preserve for the ages the glorious trail AndHowsHerBush will set.</div><div><br></div><div>No seriously, did anyone hear from Bad Dog?</div>', ''),
(1227, 610, '<div>Trail Trash SoHappyItsTuesday Run #609</div><div><br></div><div>10 Dec, 2013</div><div>Start: Hunter\'s Mill Racquet and Swim Club, Reston</div><div><br></div><div>Hares: Strokin\' My Wife Away, All The Way In, Parent\'s Weekend</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div><div>Dear Penthouse</div><div>D-VA</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>The Vaginger Monologues</div><div>And Hows Her Bush</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>SWWAAT</div><div>Little Cock</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Just Allen</div><div>Just Wayne - Virgin brought by Vaginger</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Tonight\'s Theme had something vaguely to do with werewolves because</div><div>there was supposed to be an eclipse of some kind. The Trail</div><div>descriptions said it was a solar eclipse, but my logic says that is</div><div>impossible at night?... I couldn\'t find any information on anything</div><div>scheduled to happen that evening but it was a half-moon... so maybe it</div><div>was a hemiwerewolf kinda night? Either way it was cold and the streets</div><div>and sidewalks were extra icy... including the parking lot/skating rink</div><div>we started from. We enjoyed watching wankers slip-slide across the</div><div>black-ice as they tried to maneuver into parking spots. I thought for</div><div>a moment we would need to push AHHB\'s truck out by hand with the sound</div><div>of spinning occurring from his wheels. We all gathered in close and</div><div>tried to keep warm as Strokin\' explained some trail stuff... all we</div><div>cared about was that there would be a fire at the end! Off the Hares</div><div>went and a few minutes later we slid (literally) on out after them.</div><div>The trail took us along Brittenford Dr that we had come in on before</div><div>veering into Difficult Run Stream Valley Park. I almost bit it on the</div><div>ice as I headed down the first swale crossing the stream, I thought</div><div>the folks behind me had heard my cries to god as I flailed to maintain</div><div>vertical, but I could hear them behind me doing the same thing just a</div><div>minute later! We would spend the next 2 miles basically maneuvering</div><div>around the various trails of the park. The Hares did another great job</div><div>of providing good marking given the darkness, although that damn</div><div>orange-chalk is horrible in the dark! Luckily, with the fresh snow and</div><div>the half-moon you barely needed a headlamp to see the marking on the</div><div>trees. Stuff on the ground you had to be right on top-of due to the</div><div>coloring. &nbsp;We enjoyed a nice beer-check about 1.5 miles in and then</div><div>proceeded through the stream valley before popping out onto the WO&amp;D</div><div>Trail and crossing over Hunters Mill to find a thermos full of the</div><div>shot-check. I was the first one there and grabbed a quick snort before</div><div>heading on up the trail for almost .5 a mile before an intersection</div><div>took trail down into a small stream valley. Flour became few and far</div><div>between and I spent a good 10 minutes trying to make my way alone</div><div>through this section, using the old Land-Nav Circling method until I</div><div>found some more flour hidden behind a tree. Continuing on through this</div><div>valley for about a half mile before we popped out into a subdivision</div><div>and up to a check at Sunrise Valley Dr. This check stopped us up</div><div>pretty good as the pack (which had caught up) spread out finally</div><div>finding flour to the east and wound through some housing before</div><div>dropping us back off at start where the Hares had a nice roaring fire</div><div>going for us!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>A great cold-weather jaunt through snowy woods and across streams and</div><div>valleys... how poetic. About 4.5 miles, thanks Hares!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>FBI - Vaginger</div><div><br></div><div>DFL - Baddus Doggus</div><div><br></div><div>Returners - Horse Jerker</div><div><br></div><div>Analversarries: Just Allen - 7... namings a comin\'!!!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div><br></div><div>SWWAAT - Creepy Silence of the Lambs Stuff.... Collecting leftover</div><div>foreskins to become a Jew (I don\'t know.... Udder wrote it down!)</div><div><br></div><div>Horse Jerker - Driving like a New Yorker coming skidding across the</div><div>ice into start</div><div><br></div><div>Vaginger - After all this time hashing never noticed the G (spot) on</div><div>the back of Taster\'s SUV....</div><div><br></div><div>I\'ve Fallen and I Can\'t Get it Up - Leaving his car trunk open to try</div><div>and get more heat before start... just wear an extra Jacket!</div><div><br></div><div>AHHB - Lack of Traction, trying to use the parking lot as a test-track</div><div>with the beer wagon</div><div><br></div><div>Parent\'s Weekend - For attempting a bad impression of Smaug-Stein</div><div><br></div><div>Bad Dog - for refusing to give up personal warmth for the good of others</div><div><br></div><div>Taster\'s Choice - for coming up with the idea for a Koozee that keeps</div><div>your drink cold but warms your hands, but failing to produce it for</div><div>circle.</div><div><br></div><div>Just Wayne and Strokin\'- For feeling up Vaginger.... They were just</div><div>trying to keep you warm!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>It was cold, there was more I\'m sure, but I was just hoping to get rid</div><div>of the HashSh!t... I added a headlamp to it to make up for mine that I</div><div>haphazardly destroyed at the Halloween Trail. This edition of the</div><div>HashSh!t is becoming like a Swiss Army Hash Knife... so many utilities</div><div>attached. I almost kept it &nbsp;because the song book that AHHB had</div><div>attached a few weeks ago apparently was falling off the thing the</div><div>entire way. Doc Strangelove was picking up song card over the courseof</div><div>trail that I had left like Hansel and Gretel\'s bread crumbs! So Note</div><div>to you hashers... STRONGLY SECURE the things you add to the HashSh!t</div><div>Anyway SWWAAT did something stupider... I think it was complain about</div><div>dudes? And she got it instead. Bye-Bye My HashSh!t, I\'m sure we\'ll</div><div>spend more time together sooner or later!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>We hung out for a bit because let\'s be honest... who wants to waste a</div><div>good fire!? Then headed on out... Again I didn\'t do the On-After cause I</div><div>had an early day planned for Wed. But with any hope we didn\'t manage</div><div>to get ourselves banned from wherever you wankers ended up at.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>See you next week!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div>', ''),
(1228, 608, '<div>So Happy It\'s Tuesday Trail #607, "The \'Thanksgiving Week in Herndon\' Trail" aka "The Awesomest Trail of the Year"&nbsp;</div><div>It started sprinkling on Tuesday morning and kept it up throughout the day, raining harder as each hour passed. &nbsp;By hash time, it had been pouring for hours and rivers were running through the streets. &nbsp;Several brave souls borrowed canoes and made it to start. &nbsp;</div><div>SWATT pulled into the parking lot and tried to park on a tree. &nbsp;The assembled wankers laughed. &nbsp;Lube Me Up Scotty pulled into the parking lot and tried to park on a tree. &nbsp;The assembled wankers laughed. &nbsp;</div><div>Shortly thereafter, Just Allen pulled into the parking lot and tried to park on a tree. &nbsp;The assembled wankers laughed. At this point the group consisted of five hares (The Udder Ho, Nuclear Jism, Curb Job, Free Pu$$y to Good Home, and Lube Me Up Scotty) and four wankers (And Hows Her Bush, SWATT, Just Allen, Holy F*ck). &nbsp;The entire group negotiated on who wanted to run, who wanted to walk and who wanted to go straight to the bar/Udder\'s house. &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;After determining there were no walkers present, Curb Job and Free Pu$$y bailed on their portion of trail and decided to be bag transport. &nbsp;Yes, both of them. &nbsp;In separate cars. &nbsp;For a total of four bags. &nbsp;</div><div>AHHB and Udder decided to transport the beer to the end. &nbsp;Yes, both of them. &nbsp;In separate cars. &nbsp; This left the heroes of our story, Nuclear Jism and Lube Me Up Scotty to save this wreck of a trail and turn it into the awesomest trail ever.</div><div>&nbsp;Nuke and Lube filled their flour bags and headed off into the dark, rainy, scary night all alone. &nbsp;But never fear, they had headlamps! &nbsp;It is important to point out that headlamps are not sufficient to determine the depth of puddles on a dark and rainy night. &nbsp;Nuke got around this performance flaw by sending Lube ahead and listening to her bitch as the water lapped over her shoes, then taking an alternate route. &nbsp;Ass.</div><div>&nbsp;Since I am Lube and I was saving the hash with Nuke, I do not know what the wankers did after we left. &nbsp;Probably stood around and cried like little girls. &nbsp;Or schemed on how to become the best pickle ranchers on the east coast. &nbsp;I\'m sure one of those is true.</div><div>&nbsp;Nuke and Lube ran through freezing water, sleet, strange people staring at us and Herndon to create a trail worthy of the group gathered. &nbsp;That is to say it was just over 2 miles long. &nbsp;The beer check was epic. &nbsp;The wankers huddled in a shed staring at dirty jocks. &nbsp;Not EVERY trail is this cool! &nbsp;On in was warm (the Ho abode) and the dry, lame hares welcomed Nuke and Lube with beverages, orange food and dry clothes. &nbsp;And Oreos. &nbsp;There was an Oreo incident. &nbsp;I just wanted more than one. &nbsp;But the package thwarted my every attempt to pull just one more out. &nbsp;I freaked. &nbsp;The hares gave me a "˜WTF?\' kind of look and I told them it had been a long week. &nbsp;Udder pointed out it was only Tuesday"¦ &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;We stood around in Udder\'s kitchen waiting for the pack (all three of them) to arrive. &nbsp;Finally, a headlamp ran past Udder\'s house. &nbsp;Um"¦ didn\'t the open fence kind of give an idea where to go? &nbsp;Three minutes later, the headlamp was back. &nbsp;It was Holy and we proclaimed him FBI. &nbsp;Then SWATT arrived and we proclaimed her FRB. &nbsp;Yes, we did that on purpose. &nbsp;Just Allen was DFL because he was a just. &nbsp;And last.</div><div>&nbsp;We held circle in the kitchen after everyone had changed. &nbsp;I had Udder turn down the lights so it felt more like a dark parking lot. &nbsp;We then learned that Udder changed his dining room light bulb nine times because it was so dim until he realized it was on a dimmer switch. &nbsp;The operative word there is \'dimmer.\'</div><div>&nbsp;There were many violations for the hares, but none because of the trail. &nbsp;Which (as previously stated) was awesome. &nbsp;In the middle of circle, Udder\'s sister and brother in law showed up with two little dogs "“ in for the Thanksgiving holiday. &nbsp;When asked if we needed to go "˜family friendly\' for the rest of the circle Udder yelled at his sister, "Have you ever heard a swear word?" &nbsp;She said she had and circle continued uncensored. &nbsp;AHHB brought out the hashit he had been awarded last week for effing up his trail (not everyone can be as awesome as Nuke and I). &nbsp;AHHB added a bunch of laminated song cards and a laminated trail marking card to the hashit. &nbsp;Because of these additions, Just Allen was nominated for the hashit since he doesn\'t really know any songs and needs to hare. &nbsp;Nominations closed, Just Allen was awarded the hashit, we sang the requisite song, then we sang Swing Low and just like that, the awesomest trail ever was over.</div><div>&nbsp;Lube Me Up Scotty &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1229, 609, '<div>Hash Trash SoHappyIt\'sTuesday Run #608</div><div><br></div><div>3 December, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>E.C. Lawrence Park Soccer Fields, Centreville, VA</div><div><br></div><div>Hares: The Otter Pink Meat, Matherbates, Just Allen</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Parent\'s Weekend</div><div>SWATT</div><div>Dear Penthouse</div><div>Department of Vegetable Affairs</div><div>Strokin\' My Wife Away</div><div>Beast Master (From Dayton, OH)</div><div>Little Cock</div><div>I\'ve Fallen and I Can\'t Get it Up</div><div>The Vaginger Monologues</div><div>And Hows Her Bush</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div><div><br></div><div>Virgins:</div><div>Just John Paul</div><div>Just Mike</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>It\'s that time of year again.... The decorations go up, Parking lots</div><div>gets full of trees, some of you act inappropriately at your work</div><div>parties (or the hash) and everybody breaks out their ugliest sweaters!</div><div>The pack did a pretty good job of getting into the spirit with some</div><div>pretty nice ugly-sweater game this year. We thought we were going to</div><div>be pretty secluded in the sports field parking lot until just before</div><div>start when a ton of folks started pouring into the lot for a soccer</div><div>game. &nbsp;DeVA and DP noted they had pulled in to the lot just a few days</div><div>prior for an impromptu two-person game!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>The Hares sprinted off into the soccer field and left Parents Weekend</div><div>to do chalk talk.... I hope someone got a photo of this because he</div><div>managed to squish every possible marking into a 4 foot square. It was</div><div>like a collection of bad tag jobs on the side of a DC - City wall!</div><div>After a bit we started trotting off after the hares and before we</div><div>could get our heart rates up we discovered the beer check at about a</div><div>quarter mile from start... That\'s one sure fire way to slow the pack</div><div>down! Little did we realize that the hares were about to employ</div><div>another method of accomplishing the same task. That is to, send them</div><div>through some pretty horrendous only-one-can-pass shiggy in the dark! I</div><div>had decided to keep the walkers company while they chilled (literally)</div><div>at the beer-check and then made my way onto the next section of trail,</div><div>alone. The next 3 / 4 of a mile involved climbing over some intense</div><div>overgrowth and downed trees, shimmying under rotting logs and thick</div><div>twisted vines, and generally trying to avoid tripping or snagging</div><div>yourself on any random stuff. &nbsp;Which I did twice and thankfully there</div><div>was no one there to see it happen. The hares did a great job of</div><div>marking the trail, and it really did twist and turn... the inner hare in</div><div>me swore there was probably a trail off to the right somewhere and I</div><div>could avoid all this... but gosh-darn-it, the hare went through the</div><div>trouble of climbing through this with a bag of flour. The least I</div><div>could do was follow it! I finally caught up with the pack just as the</div><div>trail busted out into apath following the Run (Big Rocky Run I think?)</div><div>and led us up to a tunnel going under Rt28. &nbsp;A few hashers headed</div><div>towards the tunnel but the hares had other plans and flour was found</div><div>on top leading us north along the west side of 28. We followed four</div><div>for about another quarter mile and then it stopped.... I\'m sure it was</div><div>there somewhere but we couldn\'t find it. Wankers were spread over</div><div>several hundred yards calling out and searching... a few false alarms</div><div>(and the ensuing bee-line towards their directions) continued to</div><div>confuse us and mess up our bearings. By the time True trail was found</div><div>way over to the west of the last check I was two hundred yards and a</div><div>junkload of shiggy away. I also could see the lights from the parking</div><div>lot.... I decided I would no longer be a trail purist and forged</div><div>northward. Luckily I ended up finding flour again and Strokin and I</div><div>made our way into the end. I guess we missed a shot check, I heard it</div><div>was delicious! All in all a shiggariffic 1.93 Miles that seemed like</div><div>4! Great Job Hares, I\'m sure it hurt you more than it hurt us!</div><div><br></div><div>We moved our gathering spot farther north in the lot to avoid</div><div>bothering the frozen-soccer players cavorting on the south fields and</div><div>then kicked off our circle.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>I started to keep some notes, but AHHB said "Don\'t Worry, I\'ll send</div><div>you all the violations". So this is what I\'ve got cause he never did</div><div>:P</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Just Allen couldn\'t win FRB because he was haring... I\'m sure that</div><div>devesatded him. It was Strokin</div><div><br></div><div>FBI: Just guessing it was SWATT</div><div><br></div><div>DFL: It\'s time to retire this and just print up an official BadDog DFL</div><div>Shirt... it will sell like hotcakes!</div><div><br></div><div>Returners: Dear Penthouse, DeptVegAffairs (except as they noted, they</div><div>had been to the start location very recently!)</div><div><br></div><div>Virgins: Brought by Otter I think? Just John Paul and Just Mike</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Analversarries:</div><div>SWATT and Mathterbates - 14,</div><div>Otter and Fallen - 21</div><div>ATWI - 98 (with 27 Hares that\'s a 28% Haring Rate</div><div>Bad Dog - 273 (with 4 Hares that\'s a 1% Haring Rate)</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Best Ugly Sweater went to SWATT. She made sure to violate all of us</div><div>who changed out of our ugly sweaters for circle... sorry SWATT, it was</div><div>cold and that sweater was soaked!</div><div><br></div><div>Hash Sh!t....</div><div><br></div><div>Somehow I ended up with this thing.... I don\'t remember why... but in</div><div>usual HashSh!t tradition I\'m sure someone else deserved it more. J</div><div>Strangely enough it was the first time since I started Hashing in 2007</div><div>that I earned the honor!</div><div><br></div><div>And just as we broke up one of Fairfax County\'s Finest rolled in... I</div><div>ducked out quick as I had a beer soaked plunger strapped to my back!</div><div>On-After was scheduled for the Buffalo Wing Factory but I couldn\'t</div><div>make it, anybody got any scoop on the Wing-fueled shenanigans?</div><div><br></div><div>On-on,</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div>', '');
