(1222, 603, '<div>So Happy It\'s Tuesday Run #602.</div><div><br></div><div>Stage #2 of Bad Dog\'s SEXfecta Analversary week (269th SHIT trail)</div><div><br></div><div>Hares:</div><div>Bad Dog and And Hows Her Bush</div><div><br></div><div>Location:</div><div>Great Falls, VA â€“ at the abode of Great Falls Hasher Pickled Peter</div><div><br></div><div>Did you know that the symbol that we in â€˜Merica call the â€œnumberâ€ or</div><div>â€œpound signâ€ is also referred to as the Octothorpe? And that the</div><div>British and other Europeans refer to it as Hash? They however are more</div><div>prone to using â€œNo.â€ to represent number and â€œÂ£â€ for pound. I for one</div><div>am glad that we are not called the Octothorpe House Harriersâ€¦. Just</div><div>doesn\'t have the same ring to it. I bet though that it won\'t be long</div><div>until we start just writing #househarriers. (Note to ATWI: Hab idea??)</div><div><br></div><div>The Pack:</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Parent\'s Weekend</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>Strokin\' My Wife Away</div><div>I\'ve Fallen and I Can\'t Get It Up</div><div>Double O Positive</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div><div><br></div><div>TURD: (Tethered Urban Running Dog)</div><div>Just Finley</div><div><br></div><div>The Trail:</div><div>The Pack met in the woods behind the home of Great Falls and DCH3</div><div>Hasher Pickled Peter, who joined us for start, but repaired back to</div><div>his Great Falls abode to be able to claim plausible deniability for</div><div>any shenanigans that might ensue during and after trail (From us? No</div><div>way?!) To be more specificâ€¦ after walking behind the house one had to</div><div>cross the mammoth sloped back yard in the dark, pick their way through</div><div>some brush, and head down a steep hill towards a camp fire that wasn\'t</div><div>visible until you were on top of it. We would also come to find out</div><div>that this was Double O Positive\'s preferred Great Falls Hunting spot</div><div>and had a few deer stands and cameras set up within a stones throw.</div><div>He pleaded for us not to waste his batteries and flash-drive space by</div><div>providing gratuitous mooning and crotch shotsâ€¦ What else are we</div><div>supposed to do at checks while the FRB\'s solve them???</div><div>As the time to send off the Hares approached Bad Dog made it known</div><div>that he didn\'t need to be sent offâ€¦.. What?!! He then went on to</div><div>describe that Circles would be Checks, and X\'s would be false trails</div><div>(Both trail markings that are NOT Native to So Happy It\'s Tuesday) I</div><div>guess when it\'s your special made-up holiday of runs you can pre-lay</div><div>and use whatever markings you want! Don\'t worry Bad Dogâ€¦ we\'ll</div><div>remember when it\'s time for end circle! On a side-note and for the</div><div>Hashing Record, I do not recall seeing him ON TRAIL at any time with</div><div>the White House Hash-Shit he received on Stage 1 of his SexFecta!</div><div><br></div><div>Three Walkers, Four Runners (a fifth would come late) and One TURD</div><div>bounded off into the forest following dollops of flour and waving good</div><div>bye to the Hares (Wait, something is not right there!) The heavy tree</div><div>cover made for a very dark trail and luckily all the pack had their</div><div>headlamps. Trail quickly crossed Nichols Run and meandered over the</div><div>river and through the woods (no grandma was in sight, sorry GILF Fans)</div><div>before busting out onto some back roads after about a half mile. We</div><div>worked our way out to Springvale Rd and were caught for a second with</div><div>a check. Trail ensued up the way with the hare\'s Modus Operandi being</div><div>the use of the Back Check into neighborhoods off the road. Before</div><div>finding the Second Back Check, I passed Parent\'s Weekend heading back</div><div>and asked â€œBack Check?â€. â€œNoâ€ he said,â€Just going back to find Silver</div><div>so she doesn\'t get lonely running all slow by herselfâ€â€¦. Luckily I\'m</div><div>Fallen was ahead and actually caught the checkâ€¦ I still think Parent\'s</div><div>was lying! We continued up Springvale, dodging speeding local vehicles</div><div>on the dark roadway with no shoulders as the trail markings bounced</div><div>from side to side of the road like some baker\'s version of PONG. After</div><div>almost a mile, trail made a sharp turn down a dark road. Literally I</div><div>mean down. Just Finley took advantage of this downhill slope and</div><div>straightaway and took off dragging me behind. As the lights from the</div><div>road disappeared and the only signs of life I could see were flickers</div><div>from houses nestled in the woods, I began to get worried about yelling</div><div>On-On at full volume, lest the local Virginian homesteaders take me</div><div>for an intruder and show off their second amendment rights! Upon</div><div>reaching the bottom of the hill Newton\'s 69th Law of Hashing proved</div><div>itself once againâ€¦. â€˜What goes down, must come up\' and now I found</div><div>myself being drug uphill with gravity working against me this time!</div><div>The road hit a dead end and trail pulled us back into the woods then</div><div>back across Nichols Creek again before hopping back out onto another</div><div>Great Falls back road. A large BN adorned the side of the road near a</div><div>drivewayâ€¦ which was confusing because in usual SHIT Markingsâ€¦ that</div><div>means the END is Near. Either way, I was not about to argue semantics</div><div>when there were beers to drink. The Hares had smartly negotiated the</div><div>use of another Great Falls hasher\'s driveway to stage the Beer truck.</div><div>As I approached the house I was bit apprehensive because AHHB had</div><div>hidden the truck in the cover of a tree (Whether this was consciously</div><div>done, I do not know.) I again started to wonder if I was about to meet</div><div>a local\'s Smith &amp; Wesson, when I heard AHHB and moved in to grab a</div><div>brew. The rest of the runner\'s rolled in, followed by the walkers and</div><div>then latecomer Horse Jerker. Unfortunately for Horse Jerker, no</div><div>checks had been marked so he had had a long evening and was ready to</div><div>quench his thirst! Bad Dog confessed that he had jacked up Walker\'s</div><div>Trail because flooding and tree damage made it now impassible. After</div><div>he decided we had become too loud and unruly we were shooed off to</div><div>continue trail. The Walkers were then carted off in the back of the</div><div>truck to Auto-Hash back to start. The Runner\'s however still had two</div><div>miles to go and took off to explore some more of the fine residential</div><div>roads of Great Falls. A jump through some woods at a cul-de-sac</div><div>provided us two more chances to cross some creeks before spitting us</div><div>back onto Utterback Store Road. Here we met Bad Dog who was waiting</div><div>for the pack to tell us he might not have laid trail very clearly for</div><div>the next little bit and tried to shout out directions like an old</div><div>hillbilly rocking in a chair outside a country gas stationâ€¦.. â€œgo on</div><div>down yonder diagonally, take a right when ya hit the ol\' fence, follow</div><div>them there fence till ya take a left at the end and keep on clearâ€¦. Ya</div><div>can\'t miss it!â€ Here\'s an ideaâ€¦ next time just lay enough flour! We</div><div>aren\'t smart enough to keep all those fancy directions in our head as</div><div>we careen haphazardly through the briars and the brambles (of which</div><div>there were PLENTY on this next Â¼ Mile of trail!) we managed to survive</div><div>the directions and floundered through the shiggy before coming out</div><div>onto Nicholsridge road and it was a straight away back to start! Way</div><div>to take us through the toughest most dangerous shiggy right in the</div><div>last half mile Bad-Dog! I clocked about 4.25 miles of various woods,</div><div>roads, and trails through Great Falls. As blood trickled down my</div><div>knees, we stumbled in to start and then made our way down the hill to</div><div>a welcoming roaring fire and commenced our circle.</div><div><br></div><div>Returners:</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Double O Positive</div><div><br></div><div>No Virgins, No Visitors</div><div><br></div><div>Analversaries:</div><div>Bad Dog! 269â€¦ only four more till your next Analversary (7x39)</div><div>The pack questioned Bad Dog about some metrics of his storied hashing</div><div>career and was able to pull from him that his record for â€˜most days</div><div>hashing in a row\' was 17! No one bothered to ask what percentage of</div><div>those were actually finished in a timely manner, however it was asked</div><div>how many gallons of milk were consumed! Also, his record for â€˜most</div><div>hashes in a week\' is 11â€¦ Way to take it to 11, Spinal Tap would be</div><div>proud (The Bandâ€¦ not the hasher!)</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Falling and I Can\'t Get it up (Two weeks in a row!)</div><div>DFL: Strokin\' My Wife Away</div><div>FBI: Silver Lining (the Only BI!, also two weeks in a row)</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div>- Double O Positive â€“ For having the Most Tree Stands Per Capita.</div><div>- Strokin\' â€“ For ADHD at Circle. Zoned out staring in the fire and</div><div>blanked out when asked for a Down-Down song!</div><div>- Parents Weekend â€“ For Over Achieving. He brought a heavy ass cooler</div><div>full of ice and beer down the hill to circle before checking to see if</div><div>AndHowsHer had already done so (He had). It was suggested he not be</div><div>allowed to leave until he had drank every oneâ€¦ but seeing as he was my</div><div>ride I advised against it.</div><div>- AndHowsHerBush- For having a Senior moment. At the pre-trail circle,</div><div>AHHB didn\'t know whether Bad-Dog had ever haired for SHIT beforeâ€¦.</div><div>However an inspection of the HareLog shows that of the 4 Hare credits</div><div>Bad Dog hasâ€¦ AHHB has been co-hair 3 times!</div><div>- Taster\'s Choice â€“ For being a Troll and taking the time to stalk the</div><div>website to discern how many times Bad Dog had hared. (Trails in 2005,</div><div>2006, 2009, 2013â€¦That\'s 4 out of 269â€¦. Or 1.5% of all SHIT trails</div><div>ranâ€¦. Looks like we are due again for a Bad Dog trail in 2020 if you</div><div>follow the mathematical sequence)</div><div>- Strokin â€“ For ventriloquy on trail by making his Ass Talk at the</div><div>Beer Check (on a side noteâ€¦ do yourself a favor and Google</div><div>â€˜Butthoven\'s Fifth\')</div><div>- Bad Dog â€“ For trying to Kill the Pack! Laying a dangerous trail</div><div>along a road with no shoulder, no street lights, heading up a hill</div><div>with speeding cars coming from the other side!</div><div>- Pack â€“ AHHB violated the pack for not fucking anyone from Great Falls!</div><div>- Bad Dog â€“ For Narcissism. Laying 6 trails in a row in order to be</div><div>able to say he was FRB 6 times!</div><div>- Bad Dog â€“ For being a cheap skate! Laying 6 trails in a row to avoid</div><div>paying the hash-cash!</div><div>- All The Way In â€“ He was sick, and was barely standingâ€¦ which is</div><div>admirable to come on out even when under the weatherâ€¦ but stay by the</div><div>fire and drink! Don\'t go out on trail!</div><div>- Bad Dog â€“ For trying to pre-lay a SHIT Trail and using other hashes</div><div>markings! Here is the way we like to do it for future reference!</div><div>http://sohappyh.s459.sureserver.com/hare_guide.php</div><div>- All The Way In â€“ If you are sick and can barely get 4 words out of a</div><div>songâ€¦. Don\'t pick a song that no one else knows so you end up having</div><div>to sing the whole thing by yourself!</div><div>- Hares â€“ What a SHIT-ty Trail! Actually it was more like a</div><div>WhiteHouse-y trail, wrong marks and pre-laid! We\'ll see if OTH will</div><div>stand for that tomorrow!</div><div><br></div><div>No Hash-Shit this weekâ€¦ it\'s a shame, it would have been nice to pass</div><div>it on to Bad Dog to carry on his next several trails of the Sexfectaâ€¦.</div><div>I hope the rest of the hashes this week learn from our mistake and</div><div>MAKE SURE YOUR HASH SHIT is there!</div><div><br></div><div>Announcements!</div><div>Bad Dog invited the pack out to The Old Brogue in Great Falls Village,</div><div>where a few wankers continued on to join him and enjoy the 10%</div><div>discount he had haggled for.</div><div>We swung low and then proceeded to have an argument about how best to</div><div>put out the fireâ€¦. After which, we complained about how we had put out</div><div>the fire instead of sticking around and enjoying itâ€¦</div><div><br></div><div>Bad Dog WILL NOT be the hare next week, SHIT Mismanagement will host a</div><div>Herndon Pub Crawlâ€¦ more details to follow. Bad Dog\'s SexFecta</div><div>continues with Over The Hump on Wednesday in Burke, Everyday Is</div><div>Wednesday on Thursday in Vienna, Mount Vernon on Saturday Morning at</div><div>Lake Accotink, and ending at Great Falls on Saturday Afternoon in</div><div>Great Falls. Join him on his Tour D\'uh Lost!</div><div><br></div><div>Hope you enjoyed the #trash</div><div><br></div><div>See ya next trail!</div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster\'s Choice</div>', ''),
