(1224, 605, '<div>A Real "Guy\'s" Trail</div><div>Trail #604: Chantilly, VA</div><div>November 5, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>"Remember, Remember</div><div>The fifth of November,</div><div>The gunpowder treason and plot.</div><div>I know of no reason</div><div>Why the gunpowder treason</div><div>Should ever be forgot."</div><div><br></div><div>Hash history lesson.... Never mind, read it yourself.</div><div>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guy_Fawkes</div><div>Lesson to be learned: Don\'t let some guys talk you into sitting in a</div><div>dark cellar with a shit-ton of gunpowder with the promise that</div><div>"They\'ll be right back to relieve you in the morning"</div><div><br></div><div>Thanks to those who went with the theme and wore masks! Next time</div><div>we\'ll have to light a bonfire and burn effigies!</div><div><br></div><div>Hares:</div><div>The Vaginger Monolouges and Taster\'s Choice</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>SWATT</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>I\'ve Fallen and I Can\'t Get it Up</div><div>Little Cock that Won\'t</div><div>Parents Weekend</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>The Otter Pink Meat</div><div>Mathterbates</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Just Allen</div><div>Just Mike</div><div><br></div><div>Location:</div><div>We started at the back of Justice Federal Credit Union in Chantilly on</div><div>a crisp autumn night. Once again, I must warn you... this account comes</div><div>from a hare and all tales of shenanigans on trail are strictly</div><div>heresay! Vaginger and I scampered off in different directions but at</div><div>least left a true trail mark for the pack to follow... This is where I</div><div>learned another haring lesson... the pack walks for two minutes... so I</div><div>shouldn\'t lay flour at start as if they were running.... (or should I....</div><div>to slow them down ;) It was brought to my attention at end that there</div><div>wasn\'t enough flower at start, so I jogged out with Mathterbates and</div><div>proved to him it was sufficiently marked. Stop chatting up the pack</div><div>during those first two minutes and keep your eyes open wankers!!</div><div>Anyhow, trail weaved around the industrial park\'s parking lots and</div><div>over towards some woods, a check gave the impression of heading into</div><div>the shiggy, but it was a farce and continued up the sidewalk to</div><div>another intersection. Trail continued west landing at another</div><div>intersection and again threw the pack off by giving the impression of</div><div>wooded shenanigans just to take them the other direction down towards</div><div>Braddock Road. Knowing that the hash has used this terrain in the past</div><div>year or so, the hares thought to trick the kennel by leading them</div><div>towards a power grid fence, last used as a beer-check by Parents</div><div>Weekend. But this trail would instead head back east on the jogging</div><div>path along Braddock where the pack was met with a Whiskey and Coke</div><div>Shot Check! As the pack left the shot check, they soon came upon a</div><div>runners/walkers split.... And as they say on VH-1 Behind the Music....</div><div>"They had the world at their fingertips... and then things went sour...</div><div>you see, in a Hare\'s mind, the trail is perfect. And just like a</div><div>military operation every contingency has been accounted for and all</div><div>I\'s dotted and t\'s crossed... but this is hubris and the downfall of</div><div>many a hare. No plan is fool-proof. The hare\'s had discussed some</div><div>distribution of responsibility and in these pre-trail talks there was</div><div>some miscommunication. The plan was to send the runner\'s down a long</div><div>Back Check that would return them to the runner walker\'s split and</div><div>true trail off behind the walkers.... That would have been great. Had</div><div>the back check been set. As I scampered by runner/walker split after</div><div>laying the first portion of trail I glanced down and smiled before</div><div>continuing on to catch up with Vaginger... beforehand Vaginger had said,</div><div>"I\'ll set the back-check" what I didn\'t realize was that the</div><div>back-check she meant was from the beer-check back out to true Trail.</div><div>So I continued on, with a chuckle at what the pack would say when they</div><div>got to the Back Check and cursed the hares.... Apparently though when</div><div>the pack got to the split the runners didn\'t let a simple thing like</div><div>NOT ONE BLOB OF FLOUR keep them from following off in the direction</div><div>the Runner\'s True-Trail pointed them.... And I mean like ï¿½\'s of a mile</div><div>worth of trying to find flour. So anyway Trail continues up into</div><div>Flat-Lick Stream Valley Park and skirted a subdivision before arriving</div><div>at a Beer-check just a short hop near a FFx County Police station...</div><div>What can I say, we hashers like to live on the edge. From here the</div><div>pack followed THE Back Check 15 back along the wooded path they came</div><div>in (and past a creepy weeping angel statue randomly placed at the</div><div>base of a tree) back to a retention pond and wound through a</div><div>subdivision with another runner/walker split then down past Cub Run</div><div>Elementary. They then headed straight back up Braddock before diving</div><div>back into the Industrial park for the home stretch back to start....</div><div>Vaginger and I knew something was up when we both came down the end</div><div>trail near the split where we figured the pack had long since passed...</div><div>only to see headlamps bobbing in the dark. We Quickly Dove into cover</div><div>and observed as the pack cursed and spit as they came back out of the</div><div>woods at the split and followed on towards the beer check... This is</div><div>where our moment of clarity occurred "Man, you must have really set a</div><div>long back check for them down there" I said to Vaginger... "Huh? You set</div><div>it?" DOH, FACE PALM.... I take the blame on this one... however to our</div><div>credit the pack arrived at the Beer Check together and generally</div><div>finished with minutes (Bad Dog excepted as usual). Just Allen, the</div><div>FRB, cruised into Finish with his hot pink shoes like he had just won</div><div>a marathon, arms stretched out over his head in celebratory fashion....</div><div>Racist!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Just Allen</div><div>FBI: SWATT</div><div>DFL: Bad Dog</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div>Otter â€“ SigOther Abuse, she wanted a piece of Mathterbates coming out</div><div>of the beer check that she tried to scratch off his nipple</div><div>Just Allen and I\'ve Fallen â€“ These two were having serious discussions</div><div>about complex mathematics outside the circle alienating the rest of us</div><div>(expect Matherbates, who wasn\'t paying attention)</div><div>SWATT- for wanting healthy food provided at circle... What, there is</div><div>fiber in the table. You can feel free to gnaw on that!</div><div>Udder â€“ Over Achieving: for bragging online about the five miles he</div><div>walked to get to the gym today.</div><div>Taster\'s Choice â€“ For trying to go Over the heads of Hashers by</div><div>singing a mathematical down-down song detailing the Quadratic Formula</div><div>(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quadratic_formula) For those that asked</div><div>here is the song....</div><div><br></div><div>(Tune: Row, Row, Row your boat)</div><div>"X equals minus b,</div><div>Plus or minus the square root,</div><div>Of b squared minus 4, a, c,</div><div>All-over two a."</div><div><br></div><div>I vow to sing this anytime I can when Mathterbates is violated!</div><div>Matherbates â€“ trying to pull some military maneuvers by outflanking</div><div>the walkers and scaring them (while zenning on no flour during the</div><div>split with no hash)</div><div>AndHowsHerBush â€“ Over Achiever, trail wasn\'t long enough for him so he</div><div>ran through the woods aimlessly scouting trail for a future hash.</div><div>Hares- What a Shitty Trail! Ok we\'ll not argue with that one. But nobody died!</div><div><br></div><div>HashShit:</div><div>Otter brought the Hash-Shit Forward to present for this week\'s</div><div>assignment and Matherbates proceeded to attempt to destroy the</div><div>tiki-pole (apparently he was sick of it being around, and took his</div><div>anger from the trail out on the poor HashShit). This of course earned</div><div>Mathterbates the first nomination for this week\'s trail... and you would</div><div>think that wanton disregard for hash-tradition would be a sure lock</div><div>for getting the hash-shit... but we were reminded by Parents of the end</div><div>of last week\'s Halloween Pub Crawl where Vaginger lost her keys on</div><div>trail and had the pack out searching only to find them at the last</div><div>place they looked. She had apparently fell out of a shopping cart</div><div>while goofing around on trail and they fell out there... wouldn\'t you</div><div>think that would be the first place to look?! The pack pretty much</div><div>unanimously threw their votes for Vaginger!</div><div>Following the Hash-Shit, things got a little weird... after beer was</div><div>spilled on the ground from the hash-shit, Bad Dog proceeded to get on</div><div>all fours and lick the ground. AndHowsHerBush chimed in with perfect</div><div>comedic timing by yelling "Bad Dog!" as the hasher of that name</div><div>proceeded to act like a bad-dog. We Swung Low and then headed on out</div><div>to Hooters as Bad Dog scrounged for all the left-over orange-food like</div><div>once again like a bad-dog at the dinner table.</div><div>I didn\'t make it to Hooters but I was later told that Just Allen</div><div>ordered a salad??? You want a salad, go to Ruby Tuesday\'s... Hooter\'s is</div><div>for wings, burgers, beer, and well.... Hooters... the only reason they</div><div>have salad on the menu is so dudes can scam their dieting girlfriends</div><div>into coming along!</div>', ''),
