(1239, 607, '<div>The "Hillbilly Hash on Tuesday" Trail</div><div>Trail #606: Reston, VA</div><div>November 19, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>Hares:</div><div>And How\'s Her Bush (and in spirit… Cum of a Sailor, I\'d Rather F*** My</div><div>Sister, "Gets Off Easy", and a hasher to not be named)</div><div><br></div><div>Location:</div><div>Safeway parking lot (South Lakes Village Shopping Center)</div><div><br></div><div>On-On-On:</div><div>Lakeside Inn Restaurant &amp; Pub</div><div><br></div><div>With this week’s trail, AndHowsHerBush wanted to pay homage to a trail</div><div>laid 8 years prior, and "re-hash" the Tuesday, May 17th 2005..."Oh</div><div>Brother, Where Art Thy Beer? Hillbilly Hash". AndHowsHer gave us the</div><div>history lesson how this was “officially” the first Hillbilly Hash in</div><div>the DC Area (predating HbH3 by several years) and that he was going to</div><div>endeavor to channel these long lost hashers as he schizophrenically</div><div>set trail. We were urged to come dressed in Hillbilly or face the</div><div>threat of an old fashun’ lynchin’…. But I felt like I was the only one</div><div>who attempted. I was head-to-toe Camo print and due to the cold</div><div>weather was sporting a Blaze Orange hoodie… all ready for Beer Season!</div><div>(ba-dum-ching!)</div><div><br></div><div>Strangely enough he (who always complains when hares do not provide</div><div>detailed directions) neglected to clarify that START would take place</div><div>in a separate back lot behind the Safeway. Hasher’s could be seen</div><div>circling the main parking lot looking for any other kindred spirit</div><div>with a twinkle of beer-lust in their eye. Luckily, most of us</div><div>soldiered on and finally found the spot, enjoying some pre-trail</div><div>fellowship next to some dumpsters and trash compactor.</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>Three Hands A’ Fistin – Visitor from Pike’s Peak H3 in Colorado</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Spitz.Cum</div><div>Little Cock that Won’t</div><div>SWATT</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Strokin’ My Wife Away</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>Parent’s Weekend</div><div>Taster’s Choice</div><div>Vaginger Monolouges</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Just Allen</div><div>Just Joe</div><div><br></div><div>The Trail:</div><div>AHHB set a check from start and then headed off behind the Safeway…</div><div>One hare…. Hmmm guess we know which way this check will solve! I</div><div>decided I was going to walk this week, having been at the ER earlier</div><div>in the day and shot up with meds (I even sported my nifty admittance</div><div>wristband still). But with this trail it didn’t really matter whether</div><div>you were a walker or runner because AndHowsHers’ checks slowed them</div><div>down enough that they never really got that far ahead of us. We worked</div><div>our way towards the dockside at Lake Thoreau, and noticed that the</div><div>Lakeside Inn (The planned On-After) was apparently no longer in</div><div>business! So much for a true reenactment of the original trail! We</div><div>continued on through some Reston townhouses crossing South Lakes Drive</div><div>and waving to a delightful Police Officer as the entire pack jaywalked</div><div>across the road into the Woods and down a hill leading towards Lake</div><div>Audubon. It’s a half-mile into trail and the walkers still have visual</div><div>on the FRB’s! The Hare proceeded to take trail up from the lake and</div><div>into the backyards of the 4 story lakefront town-mansions before doing</div><div>a sharp left up a steep-ass grassy hill. It would have been nice for</div><div>him to leave a rope or something to help pull-ourselves up this grass</div><div>covered cliff! (it wasn’t that bad, but it sure felt like it at the</div><div>end) The hill slowed down the runner’s enough to put Bad Dog with the</div><div>walkers as we trudged up the face of “Mount Audubon”. Then Bad Dog</div><div>started trying to lay some of his “world famous” game on Vaginger. The</div><div>resulting exchanges between them were of great amusement to us as we</div><div>gasped for breath during the ascent. At the top of the summit we</div><div>continued to weave through the neighborhood and seemingly all downhill</div><div>another half-mile to a beer-check stashed in the woods below Sunrise</div><div>Valley Drive. After a little time at the check, the Runner’s headed</div><div>off in a direction opposite of the start location and the Walker’s</div><div>headed the right way. At this point it was basically just under a</div><div>half mile on trail for walker’s back to start (with another hill of</div><div>course!) Apparently the Runner’s continued on another 1.5-2 miles,</div><div>through some good shiggy and even crossed a big creek. Spitz gave up</div><div>when she saw the water and using her knowledge of the area headed</div><div>straight back to start and beat the walker’s back! Walkers clocked</div><div>about 1.9 miles in just under 40 mins. Overall a great quick trail</div><div>that used some quality checks and evil hills to keep the pack together</div><div>for the majority of trail!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Parent’s Weekend</div><div>FBI: Spitz</div><div>DFL: Bad Dog</div><div><br></div><div>Our Visitor from Pikes Peak, 3 Hands A Fistin’, hasn’t hashed long</div><div>enough apparently to know any songs, and isn’t funny. So he showed us</div><div>the Colorado Full Moon instead! Seriously dudes, any song will do,</div><div>just try.</div><div><br></div><div>No Analversaries since AHHB keeps forgetting the list…. So instead he</div><div>did a down-down to celebrate the 5th consecutive week of forgetting</div><div>the list.</div><div><br></div><div>Long Time No Seers: Spitz, Just Joe, Little Cock, SWATT, Doc Strangelove.</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div>Spitz – “Why You No Listen!” Two minutes after AHHB left (having just</div><div>explained his solo-haring philosophy for the night) Spitz asks “So who</div><div>is AndHowsHers co-hare tonight?) (** See HashShit nomination later)</div><div>Bad Dog – Forever Alone. As the pack moved into the beer check, Bad</div><div>Dog managed to lose trail 15 yards away from an assembled group of</div><div>wankers drinking!</div><div>AHHB – Attempted Murder. Forgot to leave an Oxygen Tank for the</div><div>walkers after the mountaineering expedition on trail.</div><div>Taster’s Choice – for trying to infect the hash with whatever was</div><div>killing him this morning at the ER.</div><div>Just Joe – Decided he would try to find out where the Beer Check was</div><div>by climbing up towards a road to look for a street sign… instead of</div><div>just asking any of the third of the pack that lives or has lived in</div><div>Reston!</div><div>Udder – TMI. Let everyone know that he ALWAYS leaves his “trunk” open</div><div>for the hash!</div><div>Spitz – Making our visitor feel unwelcome by chastising him for not</div><div>remembering 6” in Colorado. I’m sure he couldn’t forget 12” though!</div><div>(For clarification: 6” is apparently a hasher there)</div><div>SWATT – As usual, she just wants to be violated and begged for it…</div><div>your wish is our command.</div><div>Just Joe – Medfield School for the Gifted Diploma….. He spent a good</div><div>minute trying to twist off the pop-off cap for the Orange Food.</div><div>Just Allen – Couldn’t Cum on demand (with a hash song for Just Joe)</div><div>Taster’s Choice – for being a bad choir director…. Ok so here I will</div><div>rant for a second. I enjoy the violations in circle just as much as</div><div>the next, but this particular violation and attitude bothers me</div><div>every-time it comes up… and I’ve seen it happen here and abroad... Let</div><div>me explain… So, I tried to help Just Allen when he was looking all</div><div>“Deer in the headlights” when asked for Hash Song. I felt bad for him</div><div>and remembered what it was like to be a new hasher and have those</div><div>songs swimming around in your head and getting stage fright when</div><div>called upon out of the blue. So I snuck over and whispered “just say</div><div>‘Someone’s in my Sister’s Vagina’ and everybody else will chime in.”</div><div>So he did, and the pack started singing… but a few stalwarts started</div><div>jeering and shouted ‘He’s singing it wrong!!”…. All these songs we</div><div>sing in general are bastardizations of old folk songs, drinking songs,</div><div>and children’s melodies. And each song has many variations on it.</div><div>However someone wants to sing a song, as long as it’s some portion or</div><div>even if it’s not, let em sing it! At Interamerica’s Hash this Summer</div><div>in Panama I saw a guest RA belittle a hasher who only knew one song,</div><div>and that was the only song his very old kennel sings… because it used</div><div>different lyrics from the version the RA was familiar with. Half the</div><div>songs hasher’s warble I knew from my Fraternity Days in college (often</div><div>with varied and sometimes better lyrics, and usually with more melody)</div><div>Anyway What I’m saying is, let people sing what they gonna sing. It’s</div><div>ok to be a little different. If you berate those who try you just</div><div>discourage them from doing so. More love, less song elitism, more</div><div>songs, more beer. Rant Done.</div><div>Just Joe – For being Waaaay to Eager to drink out of his new shoes. He</div><div>was upset that no one called him on them… so he called himself out on</div><div>it instead…. We applied the fool-proof Gravity test and proved the</div><div>Shoe had no “Sole”. The pack graciously added various liquids to the</div><div>shoe and you know the rest. (See OnAfter description)</div><div>Bad Dog – Worst Pick up Lines of the night on trail. Including ‘I bet</div><div>I can convince you to take some clothes off’…. Has that one ever</div><div>worked for you?</div><div>Udder – Racist! He was wearing his Disney Wine and Dine Half Marathon</div><div>Swag in Circle!</div><div>Strokin My Wife Away – Was flinging his balls (of the cheesy variety)</div><div>at Vaginger.. What is this.. a fourth grade food fight!</div><div>ATWI – Song Fail! He froze up just like Just Allen… it’s ok ATWI is</div><div>new to hashing, he stole all those patches from somebody else.</div><div>AHHB – Spitz apparently thought that AndHowsHer used too much flour on</div><div>trail?? (Is that even possible?)</div><div>Spitz – Some Nerve! for Spitz to make that last violation after the</div><div>last hash she hared in May hardly used any flour!!</div><div><br></div><div>Which brings us to HashShit!</div><div>Last week’s Winner Strokin’ added a Trail Marking guide to help</div><div>alleviate the Carrier from having any issues following flour on trail.</div><div>(he was falsely accused by the walkers last week of laying a check-8</div><div>instead of a B-Check… it was proven by the runners to be baseless</div><div>slander!!)</div><div>3 Hands a Fistin’ – For getting ridiculously bloodied on trail… no one</div><div>else seemed to have a scratch!</div><div>Spitz – For vehement denial of her spiritual blondeness</div><div>Udder/Vaginger – For dragging the good(?) name of Strokin’ through the</div><div>mud last week.</div><div>Little Cock – for trying to nominate Strokin’ again for putting Duct</div><div>Tape on the Hash Shit… when it was actually Vaginger’s addition! Why</div><div>won’t we just let this man be, hasn’t he suffered enough character</div><div>assassination!</div><div>AHHB – now for a real violation… for not checking to see if the</div><div>On-After location was even open for business (it recently shut down</div><div>and was closed up…) It’s ok though, the pack decided at the beer check</div><div>to go to Glory Days instead.</div><div><br></div><div>And In honor of all the many hare’s he embodied this evening…</div><div>AndHowsHerBush was out big winner!</div><div><br></div><div>This week I actually went on to the On-After where our antics</div><div>continued into the evening. Before heading into the bar I was nice</div><div>enough to leave an artistic sculpture of mixed media on Parents</div><div>weekend’s dash board. I called it “Fruit of my Loins”… and it was</div><div>constructed a BananaGrams Bag and two oranges I found in his passenger</div><div>seat. I think you can figure it out ;) I hope the shop-goers enjoyed</div><div>the beauty of the art. Once in the bright lights of the restaurant it</div><div>looked like AHHB had taken a money shot to the face with the bits of</div><div>dried flour he still had stuck in the nooks and crannies of his mug!</div><div>As we got him talking about the laying of flour that night he admitted</div><div>he was just leaving beer check when the runners came up and had to</div><div>hide in the woods to stay unnoticed. Meanwhile, Just Joe could have</div><div>been denied access to the bar due to the drunkenness of his shoes,</div><div>squishily plodding through the room oozing out booze with every step!</div><div>Vaginger demanded she be given red-headed sluts, and someone suggested</div><div>just go look in the mirror in the bathroom. She however wanted more</div><div>than just one… acceptable hash-behavior! With Spitz’ giant skull cap</div><div>she looked like she was only a shopping cart away from being a bag</div><div>lady. A fun rag tag group we were, and after 45 mins or so I had to</div><div>leave. Anyone have any further stories of the On-After to share? Next</div><div>week it’s ALMOST TURKEY DAY!!!</div><div><br></div><div>On-on,</div><div>Taster’s Choice</div>', ''),
