(1249, 625, '<div>Wankers!</div><div>So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers Run #624</div><div>Behind Kilroy&apos;s, March 25th 2014</div><div>Hares: Stab My Cock, Lush of the Irish, Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div><br></div><div>I was so happy to be back from 6 weeks away from y&apos;all I decided to</div><div>hare so I wouldn&apos;t have to see any of you on trail! Also another</div><div>prodigal son returned as Stab My Cock hit up his first hash since</div><div>getting back from a 10 month vacation over seas in a rocky outpost</div><div>currently being vacated of Americans. Lush of the Irish rounded out</div><div>our haring trio to make up for the ugliness of the rest of us. We</div><div>attempted a late St Patricks Theme, but you people were lame and left</div><div>us as the only ones wearing green!</div><div><br></div><div>Imagine our surprise when we came to scout the Sunday before and there</div><div>was blue flour and random hash marks layed about Wakefield Park?? It</div><div>seemed The White House Hash House Harriers were in the process of</div><div>using the same area for trail.... so we followed some bits of the</div><div>trail and skirted past their circle as not to interrupt their</div><div>debauchery and continued to scout out the remainder of trail.</div><div><br></div><div>Come Tuesday and it had started snowing earlier that afternoon and</div><div>kept going into the evening.... this was gonna be fun! The Wankers</div><div>started showing up and immediately headed into Kilroy&apos;s to avoid</div><div>standing in the snow... I stood in the lot and directed hashers to go</div><div>inside and we actually blessed the hares inside the pub before sending</div><div>us on our way! Off we went in the falling snow...I love hashing in</div><div>snow... I HATE haring in snow... so much extra work to make false</div><div>footprints and walk backwards, and climb places to avoid your damn</div><div>trail being followed.... also the terrain looks VERY different when</div><div>its blanketed in snow! some of trail was definitely NOT what I</div><div>scouted.</div><div><br></div><div>Since I only layed trail I don&apos;t know what silly things happened when</div><div>and if the pack ever left Kilroy&apos;s. I have a sneaking suspicion that</div><div>they just waited an hour and snuck around the side to trick us.</div><div><br></div><div>Trail went across Braddock and into the wilds of Wakefield park,</div><div>crossing a small creek and winding around the trails north to a check</div><div>on a road. It continued down around the back of the activity center</div><div>and then around the tennis courts and back into the woods. A Green</div><div>Jello-Shot Check was found underneath a power line tower and then</div><div>trail led up a hill towards 495..... BACk CHECK! I hope ATWI got that</div><div>one :)</div><div>Trail continued across the Power Easement and then dove into the woods</div><div>again heading straight for Accotink Creek and a beer Check hidden</div><div>under a log on the the sandy beach of the waterway.</div><div>Next Trail followed the creek before crossing at a fording point and</div><div>crossing back again a few hundred feet down on a treacherously snow</div><div>covered log.... Much to my dismay I was apparently the only one who</div><div>actually took that route... WEAK SAUCE HASHERS! It took me about 5</div><div>minutes of running to feel my toes again. The trail continued south</div><div>and worked towards Braddock Rd going underneath and winding back</div><div>through the neighborhood up an intensely long incline before spewing</div><div>back into the parking lot whence we started. Over all somewhere around</div><div>3.25 miles give or take a back check. The snow had stopped and we</div><div>congregated up in the usual spot.</div><div><br></div><div>We had a good size crowd given the weather and they were a lively</div><div>bunch.... and I can hardly remember who was there. About 12 of us I</div><div>think? Two Virgins brought by Lush of the Irish. Semen On The Pew, a</div><div>long-time DC Hasher, but apparently has NEVER ran with So Happy Its</div><div>Tuesday joined us. Coincidentally, he was the hare on my virgin trail</div><div>in 2007. Except that was in the summer, and not snowing! The Pack</div><div>drank and violated each other (wink, wink) I swear I should have just</div><div>put a chair in the middle of circle because the Hares were in just</div><div>about every violation group! The Hash Shit was given... I almost had</div><div>it for trying to sing the wrong song, but it went to whoever had it to</div><div>begin with... again, can&apos;t remember who. I tried to violate people</div><div>for not wearing green, but the greenies were in such minority that the</div><div>pack revolted and refused to acknowledge the violation! We Swung Low,</div><div>and moved on to the bar for Seafood Night.... but this time I was lame</div><div>and had to go home cause I had family visiting that I had abandoned</div><div>for the evening.</div><div><br></div><div>Looking forward to seeing you wankers again tonight! (Except Parent&apos;s</div><div>Weekend, who is sick and doesn&apos;t want to take my advice to push</div><div>fluids(beer) to get better)</div><div><br></div><div>ALSO We have openings in the Hare-Line! HARE or else ATWI will put the</div><div>SH!T in SH!tty trail.</div>', ''),
(1250, 626, '<div>April 1, 2014</div><div>The "April Fools Rush In" Trail</div><div>Eakin Community Park/Accotink Stream Valley Park, Tobin Rd Entrance.</div><div><br></div><div>Hares:</div><div>Close Your Eyes and Hope For the Breast</div><div>Meat the Parents</div><div>Wookin Pa Nub</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>Udder Ho</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>Deer Penthouse</div><div>Department of Vegetable Affairs</div><div>Amber Alert</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Little Cock that Won&apos;t</div><div>I&apos;ve Fallen and I Can&apos;t Get it Up</div><div>Nuclear Jism</div><div>Thanks, But I Can&apos;t Fit It In</div><div>Fingerrrrr</div><div>Vaginger Monolouges</div><div>How Big is Your Flower</div><div>Osama Bin Hashing</div><div>Bumspringa</div><div>Super Lonely Ultra Tramp</div><div>Cheap Ass Gigalo</div><div>Ginger Snaps</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Becuz He Can</div><div>Cheese Jizz</div><div>Fudd Mucker</div><div>And Hows Her Bush</div><div>Up My Butt With a Firetruck</div><div><br></div><div>Just John</div><div>Just Austin</div><div>Just Anne</div><div><br></div><div>The largest pack of the year assembled in the parking lot of the local</div><div>park, wondering where the beer was. Unfortunately due to traffic it</div><div>didn&apos;;t make it till just as we took off. A few smart hashers were</div><div>forward thinking enough to stash a few cans in their bags before</div><div>heading out the pack and were able to quench their thirst to the</div><div>envious stares of those who didn&apos;t prepare as well!</div><div>It was a beautiful night, the complete opposite of the previous week&apos;s</div><div>snow-hash. Many chose to dress down with the great temperatures but</div><div>this would prove to be a poor choice later once we made it into the</div><div>shiggy. The hares went on their way off in two different directions</div><div>leaving us to think that this was the start of a very long April</div><div>Fool&apos;s Joke! While there is no certain history behind the April Fool&apos;s</div><div>Traditions, any hasher can tell you that Hare&apos;s like to treat every</div><div>hash like an April Fools!We took the time to try and get to know the</div><div>large amount of returners and the few visitors that graced us with</div><div>their presence. Being as Far East in SH!T territory as we were, there</div><div>was a large contingent of more Urban DC Hashers!</div><div>At the direction of our RA Udder, the pack ambled off behind some</div><div>sports fields and into what can only be described as a thorny swamp.</div><div>There was to be no running for the next quarter mile as we slogged</div><div>through the mushy mud and attempted (mostly unsuccessfully) to avoid</div><div>the large amount of spiky plants and vines that populated the area.</div><div>The FRBs were the ones who had the joke played on them because trail</div><div>made a turn and headed back to the fields! The slower members of the</div><div>pack short cutted back over and probably spared themselves some pain.</div><div>After finally making it back to a real gravel trail the pack could</div><div>again pick up some speed and headed again NW into the park&apos;s wooded</div><div>expanse. The wily hares took us up a steep incline only to come back</div><div>down to the path again a quarter mile later then slowed the pack down</div><div>with a Back check after a large group crossed over Prosperity Avenue ,</div><div>the pack back-tracked and many headed north along some paths... I was</div><div>skeptical and went south along the Creek to find some flower on a play</div><div>ground and Sounded the ON-ON! Some great hashing terrain along</div><div>Accotink Creek here, with a nice water crossing, lots of downed trees,</div><div>and all sorts of branches, divots, and bushes to act as obstacles in</div><div>our path to beer. We meandered south-east along the creek for a good</div><div>3/4 mile before an abrupt direction change back across the creek up a</div><div>steep embankment (Thanks ATWI for helping me up!) I managed to put my</div><div>knee straight in the blob of flour on the muddy creekside hill and</div><div>ended up with dough there from my wet legs.</div><div>We stumbled across the beer check as we broke back out onto a path,</div><div>the walkers has raided the supply and left a bunch of empties at the</div><div>top. The Runner&apos;s rationed the few remaining beers between themselves</div><div>before heading south down the path and reaching a check when the path</div><div>met Woodburn Rd. Some flour was found across the road in the park but</div><div>after a few blobs didn&apos;t continue. Some wankers headed down the road</div><div>only to realize they were following ash from some road flares and not</div><div>flour. Finally the pack found trail heading up the road and they</div><div>continued on for half a mile trying to avoid being hit by speeding</div><div>oncoming traffic as there were no sidewalks or shoulders for</div><div>protection (How did we not Safety Third Violate the Hares!!). we</div><div>finally checked west down into a neighborhood, enjoying the hilliness</div><div>that makes Northern Virginia so quaint (but hard on the legs!). As the</div><div>sunset against the west we turned north up (a hill) Beverly Rd and</div><div>passed over Tobin Rd. Wait a minute!!! Start is a quarter mile west of</div><div>us... why are we going north??!! Damn Hares, better have something</div><div>good for us! A quarter mile later after winding through a townhome</div><div>community we found out that they did and were treated to a second Beer</div><div>check!! Meet the Parents and Close Your Eyes, welcomed us into their</div><div>backyard and provided us with the beverage of our choice (Beeer!) It</div><div>was starting to get chilly so after an elongated beer check (What is</div><div>this, White House H3?) It was good beer and fellowship, but we had a</div><div>circle to get to (and clean clothes!) The Walkers headed straight</div><div>south and then back to start while the runner&apos;s swooped up north and</div><div>down by Inova Hospital before shooting a halfmile back west back to</div><div>start. We got circled up, filled our vessels and then toasted our own</div><div>stupidity!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Nuclear Jism</div><div>FBI: Vaginger</div><div>DFL: Bad Dog (who was belligerent about being awarded the title)</div><div><br></div><div>We had some Analversarries!</div><div>(7) Osama Bin Hashing</div><div>(21) Close your Eyes</div><div>(42) Taster&apos;s Choice and Horse Jerker</div><div>(49) Vaginger</div><div>(259) Little Cock</div><div>Get a Life Get a Life Get a Life Life life!</div><div><br></div><div>Violations included:</div><div>The Hares - for googling the start directions and putting the wrong</div><div>info up, causing Just Anne to spend two extra hours trying to get here</div><div>from the Metro!</div><div>Bumspringa - New Shoes!!!</div><div>AndHowsHerBush - for wearing out the batteries in his vibrating metal</div><div>toy (the beer truck!)</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice - for repeatedly banging his head into the back hatch</div><div>of his SUV (Ouch!)</div><div>D-Va - for staying dressed all trail (Hares should have been violated</div><div>for not leaving the appropriate trail markings to remedy that</div><div>situation!)</div><div>Doc Strangelove - for rolling up to start and leaning out to tell the</div><div>pack (and hares) that we were at the wrong parking lot for start.</div><div>Apparently he knows better than the ones who set the trail!</div><div>Nub - For thinking all thin white guys with beards look the same and</div><div>confusing Little Cock and Just Austin!</div><div>Hares - Finally violated for the absence of tit-checks so Just Anne</div><div>obliged by providing her own since she missed trail!</div><div><br></div><div>There were a few more violations but I can&apos;t read my own writing so</div><div>they must not have been that funny. We took hats off, dropped the pots</div><div>on the ground, and swaaaaaaaanng looooooooow!</div><div><br></div><div>On-after was a Grevey&apos;s, wish i could have made it but the extended</div><div>beer breaks (which i thoroughly enjoyed!) made it so I had to get on</div><div>back home. I&apos;m sure we tore the place up and have been banned from</div><div>ever returning. I look forward to hearing the stories at this week&apos;s</div><div>hash!</div><div><br></div><div>Great Trail, tremendous shiggy, and glad to see the masses waking up</div><div>from winter hibernation and joining us on Tuesdays to get</div><div>(de?)hydrated!</div><div><br></div><div>On-on,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div>', ''),
(1251, 627, '<div>April 8, 2014</div><div>So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers Run #626</div><div>"The You&apos;ll Be Sorry!" Hare-raiser&amp;#39;s Revenge Trail</div><div>Location: Shirley Gate Rd and Braddock Rd, Fairfax, VA</div><div>Hares: All The Way In, Anti-I</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>SWWAAT</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>Deer Penthouse</div><div>D-Va</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Nuclear Jism</div><div>Vaginger Monolouges</div><div>Just John</div><div>Lush of the Irish</div><div>Stab my Cock</div><div>Just Austin</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>And Hows Her Bush</div><div>Cheap Ass Gigalo</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Just Ann</div><div>Little Cock that Won&apos;t</div><div><br></div><div>Our illustrious Hare-Raiser, All The Way In, vowed to make the pack</div><div>sorry because no one had volunteered to hare this week causing him to</div><div>have to pull a run out of his ass for us. He threatened that the trail</div><div>would be full of soul-sucking shiggy and that we would be merciless.</div><div>And of course, wankers be like &apos;Blah blah blah, ATWI, how many beer</div><div>checks will we have?&apos;. Hell hath no furry like a hare-raiser scorned!</div><div><br></div><div>Anyways, I don&apos;t live all that far from start but left at the same</div><div>time I usually do.. so I rolled up to start just as ATWI was finishing</div><div>setting up the fluorescent On-On signs. SWWAAT was already there and I</div><div>shared my beers with them as we commented on the Hobo-camp a few</div><div>hundred yards up the road. If they can squat here then for damn sure</div><div>can we hash without any official interference. Ha, well we thought so</div><div>at least!</div><div><br></div><div>SWAAT proceeded to bemoan the fact that she had to work the night</div><div>shift so she would try and get her drinking in early! ATWI offered up</div><div>a Shot Check at start in a weak attempt to slow the pack down before</div><div>they even took off! Deer Penthouse and D-Va rolled up with Diva</div><div>hanging out the window to explain that she might already be drunk!</div><div>More wankers continued to assemble and AndHowsHerBush even showed up</div><div>BEFORE the pack left! We blessed the hares and shooed them off to go</div><div>lay the trail and continued our general Bull sh!tting for several more</div><div>minutes. Luckily Doc Strangelove came in a little late and announced</div><div>that he saw the hares laying a Bad Trail over Braddock Rd so we had</div><div>the first check halfway solved before even leaving start! Note to</div><div>Hares... don&apos;t make "On out" direction the way that people have to</div><div>come in to get to start!</div><div><br></div><div>A little rendition of Father Abraham warmed up our legs, but I just</div><div>kept going left for everything because I still had a beer in my right</div><div>hand.... gotta prioritize! and off we went shortcutting to Braddock to</div><div>the check Doc warned us about. And still some wankers crossed Braddock</div><div>road?! We never learn do we? The rush-hour drivers were confused by</div><div>the pack of wankers crossing each possible direction at the Shirley</div><div>Gate Road intersection before someone found trail in the woods across</div><div>Shirley gate and off we dove into the GMU Owned plot of land there.</div><div>Trail wound around trees and up and down some small hills and hollows</div><div>with the hare slowing us down by use of star burst checks.. We would</div><div>run up on the intersection mark and then there would be trail marks</div><div>going 3-4 directions straight out on the trees as far as the eye could</div><div>see. It was like a house or mirrors, trail everywhere you looked! We</div><div>finally figured out their MO was going west along the ridge of stream</div><div>valley and then we dipped down into a depression with a burned out</div><div>tipped over VW Bug for Beer Check. Horse Jerker had shortcutted and</div><div>thought he was being all suave by running past the check up on the</div><div>ridge yelling On-On, we just laughed as we let him keep going to solve</div><div>the next check while we enjoyed a beverage or two. Besides the usual</div><div>beer, the hares also left some of that Bud-a-rita stuff. How Classy!</div><div><br></div><div>The Walkers Split off from the runners at the beer check and stayed</div><div>in the woods (theoretically... we&apos;ll get to that later) while the</div><div>running pack hopped up a hill onto some streets and continued down the</div><div>residential area before circling a retention pond through some shiggy</div><div>and then getting stumped at a check in front of the Christian School.</div><div>The holier-than-thou soccer-moms in the parking lot seemed confused by</div><div>our bewildered stares and RU? calls as we tried to figure out where</div><div>the flour went next! We finally found it in the most likely place...</div><div>straight down into a bramble infested creek valley. I mean, that&apos;s</div><div>what I would do if I was haring! As we slowly picked our way through</div><div>along the waterway the dogs from houses to our right bellowed at us ,</div><div>most likely because I&apos;m pretty sure we were blatantly trespassing, but</div><div>they were trained well and stayed up on their porches overlooking us.</div><div>(The latter end of the pack would come across their owners when they</div><div>finally caught up, story in violations!) The Hares were nice enough to</div><div>take us out of the thicket and up a slope into the athletic fields of</div><div>the school. but this respite was short lived as we headed back into</div><div>the woods (and into private property again probably!) We were very</div><div>near the spot that Little Cock and Lush met the infamous Angry</div><div>Crossbow Wielding Resident back in Dec 2012. You&apos;ll have to ask them</div><div>for that story! We continued back by some other nice big expensive</div><div>houses overlooking park land and then saw something fluorescent ahead.</div><div>The terrain started to look familiar and we realized we were just NE</div><div>of the beer check and that was the Walkers (with Little Cock in a</div><div>bright yellow SH!T shirt) STILL at the beer check! We had managed to</div><div>slowly pick our way through over a mile of shiggified trail and they</div><div>hadn&apos;t budged (They had however been drinking so it was acceptable</div><div>hash behaviour!). The runners continued pushing forward bouncing along</div><div>the stream bank until pushing out of the valley and up onto a road as</div><div>trail headed back towards Shirley Gate Road. We crossed over the busy</div><div>road and found trail along the backside of some church... whatever it</div><div>was we had to slog through some pretty mushy, muddy, grass before</div><div>pushing back into the woods where we were welcomed by a second beer</div><div>check!</div><div><br></div><div>At this point in trail, the sun had finally set, head lamps were</div><div>clicking on, and we gathered around the cooler and discussed how fun</div><div>trail had been up to this point..... we jinxed ourselves. The next</div><div>mile of trail was pretty brutal... this is where ATWI got his revenge.</div><div>It started off okay with some fun log leaps and good terrain, but the</div><div>added darkness mixed with a seriously thicker level of greenbriars led</div><div>to some pretty intense yelps of pain (I even heard AHHB complaining</div><div>that there was too much Shiggy!) We broke out from the woods onto an</div><div>access road near the Jewish School and passed over the athletic field,</div><div>thinking we were in the clear but then we penetrated the woods again</div><div>into a briar patch that would have made Brer&apos; Rabbit Scared. There was</div><div>no running at this point, it was straight up picking your way through</div><div>hoping for a few seconds of pain free movement before the next thorn</div><div>got ya!</div><div><br></div><div>Soon the lights and sounds from the road appeared and we broke out</div><div>onto the street we started from! The End was in sight. We found a nice</div><div>open clearing near a radio tower and waited for the rest of the pack</div><div>to gather!</div><div><br></div><div>Another great trail by ATWI, and if you want to save your legs, arms,</div><div>and faces, from further wounds SIGN UP TO HARE. Lots of great shiggy,</div><div>plenty of beverages, and no one got arrested (barely)</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Just Austin</div><div>FBI: SWAAT</div><div>DFL: Bad Dog</div><div><br></div><div>Analversaries: (14) Deer Penthouse and Department of Vegetable Affairs</div><div><br></div><div>Violations:</div><div>- MisManagement: Dialing (202) PudJam0 will get you this: "So Happy</div><div>It&apos;s Tuesday&apos;s next trail is: Trail #534 ~ July 17, 2012 in Chantilly,</div><div>VA... The hares are: "Herpicles&amp;quot; and "The Udder Ho"...</div><div>- Special Violation for our HareRazor (ATWI)... (strike the violins)</div><div>Whining about having to do ALL the trails... not finding anyone to do</div><div>trail... some hare counts: "AHHB" (8), "Parent&amp;#39;s Weekend" (8), "ATWI"</div><div>(7), "The Udder Ho" (6), "Taster&amp;#39;s Choice" (4).</div><div>- "Department of Vegetable Affairs" (D-Va) was convinced that</div><div>&apos;someone&amp;#39; was pregnant... She could not remember who it was... but she</div><div>heard this last week!! On April Fool&apos;s Day!!</div><div>- "Deer Penthouse" for keeping the walkers from getting arrested. A</div><div>local homeowner had decided to yell her displeasure at our presence</div><div>whilst the hind end of the pack went by (or on) her property. She</div><div>apparently started videotaping the wankers!</div><div>- "SWAAT (an ex-police officer) for trying to get the walkers</div><div>arrested. Tack on the HARES for all the "Do Not Trespass" signs.</div><div>- "Just Austin" for being a &apos;p*ssy&amp;#39;.</div><div>- HARES: "Tit Checks"? Really? That&apos;s like waiting for "SWAAT" to get</div><div>everyone arrested!!</div><div>- "The Little C*ck That Won&apos;t" and "Lush of the Irish" for their</div><div>interpretation of being homeless... setting up camp at the VW &apos;Beer</div><div>Check&apos;.</div><div>- "Virginger Monologues" for having a pop-tart still in her sign-in</div><div>book that dates back THREE MONTHS!!</div><div>- "Bad Dog" for doing the whole trail on all fours.</div><div>- "D-Va" for arguing that she did not need a flashlight and a few</div><div>minutes later... gets slapped in the face with a branch.</div><div>- "Cheap Ass Gigolo" for trying NOT TO PAY!! (Cheap Ass!!)</div><div><br></div><div>On-After was to be at Brion&apos;s Grill in the University Mall a few miles</div><div>east, but I had an early morning and had to split! I hope you all</div><div>scared the little college bros and co-eds! I wasn&apos;t the last to leave</div><div>the end-site though as Vaginger and Just John were still leaning up</div><div>against her car with no visible hands so I don&apos;t know if they ever</div><div>made it to Brion&apos;s or not! Maybe they gave the bums a free show?</div><div><br></div><div>Come on out back to Fairfax/Centreville next week as I hare a Blood</div><div>Moon - Angel of Death &amp; Taxes Trail with Doc Strangelove,</div><div>AndHowsHerBush, and the haring debut of Just Austin (which means ATWI</div><div>will have to take over as FRB!)</div><div><br></div><div>Start is at the Stringfellow Soccer Park (SOUTH of 66, NOT the</div><div>commuter lot), On-after at Red Rocks Cafe and Tequila Bar! I promise</div><div>shiggy, beer, shots, and debauchery as we crash Parent&apos;s Weekend&apos;s</div><div>back yard when he isn&apos;t home!</div><div><br></div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div>', ''),
(1252, 628, '<div>So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday</div><div>Trail #627</div><div>April 15, 2014</div><div>"Blood-moon, Angel of Death and Taxes Trail!"</div><div><br></div><div>Stringfellow Soccer Fields, Fairfax/Centreville/Chantilly (it&apos;s</div><div>seriously a quarter mile away from all three!)</div><div><br></div><div>Hares: Taster&apos;s Choice, Doc Strangelove, AndHowsHerBush, and Just</div><div>Austin (VIRGIN HARE)</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Nuclear Jism</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Spew Me Father Fore I Have Skin</div><div>Semen in Every Port (visitor and late-cummer)</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div><br></div><div>April 15th, the dreaded tax day! And this year it also happens to fall</div><div>on a Blood Moon (which no one in the DMV could see due to overcast</div><div>weather) and the Judeo-Christian Holiday of Passover (Pesach) where</div><div>they celebrate the Angel of Death passing-over the houses of the</div><div>Hebrew Slaves kept in Egyptian Captivity and not killing the first</div><div>born of each household (The Egyptians, with their lack of lamb&apos;s blood</div><div>over their doors, were not as lucky.) Soooo I decided to go with an</div><div>Angel of Death and Taxes (in Wheel of Fortune Before &amp; After fashion)</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice (myself) was haring so the weather was meant to be</div><div>sh!tty! (See two weeks ago... and then make it colder and wetter) A</div><div>steady rain fell on us at start as wankers waited in their cars to</div><div>avoid the just above freezing temps. By the time the hares were ready</div><div>to split, sleet had begun falling, and before trail was done it was</div><div>straight up snow coming down like the 7th Plague of Fire and Ice! The</div><div>hare&apos;s were a little worried that SH!T has gotten soft when (at the</div><div>time of our departure) the hare to pack ratio was 4:3. In sight of</div><div>that we decided to re-evaluate the trail plan, chop off about half of</div><div>it, and combine walkers and runners earlier than planned. Don&apos;t worry</div><div>plenty of shiggy and beer was still available! Luckily two other</div><div>wankers showed up a tad late.</div><div><br></div><div>Since I was the hare, I will only be able to regale you with a recount</div><div>of what trail was for us as we set it, and the stories I heard from</div><div>you wankers following! Luckily only two of you actually finished trail</div><div>as planned so I won&apos;t give too much detail so I can use it again!!</div><div><br></div><div>So... Trail... On out to soccer fields... into some brush and a check on</div><div>Stringfellow Rd. Trail continued to a check at Autumn Willow before</div><div>diving into some woods and giving the pack a respite from the sleet</div><div>falling. Over logs, up hills, down into a hollow and through some</div><div>serious thorns the trail wound before settling on a check next to</div><div>stream..... stream isn&apos;t quite the right word given the amount of rain</div><div>from the day before... it was up past my knees and with a slight current</div><div>as I trudged through to lay a very clear true-trail arrow on the other</div><div>bank. Only two members of the pack decided to push through and</div><div>continue to follow trail along a civil war era road bed. The others</div><div>blew through a bad trail mark and continued strolling until they ran</div><div>into Doc Strangelove who was setting the On-in trail.... Can you call it</div><div>snaring the hare when you weren&apos;t on trail? These wankers proceeded to</div><div>wander around for the next hour in the snow following parts of trail</div><div>backwards to a beer check that Doc had forgot to mark. We&apos;ll get to</div><div>them later, just imagine that they are cold and wet with no beer for</div><div>now. Back to The true-trailer&apos;s (Spew Me Father and Semen) who found</div><div>themselves at a check, it would be discerned later that Spew Me</div><div>managed to pick the wrong way at every check on trail. Just Austin,</div><div>who was giddy with excitement at his first opportunity to hare, used</div><div>setting each bad-trail as an opportunity to stretch out his legs and</div><div>get a good jog in... translation; the checks were not short if you went</div><div>the wrong way. Spew Me clocked over 4 miles for this maybe 2.5 mile</div><div>trail... lesson to be learned? Don&apos;t go the wrong way! We were expecting</div><div>about 4-5 wankers on trail but with only 2, the checks slowed them</div><div>down more than we hoped! Walkers and runners trail split here... but no</div><div>walkers were on trail at this point so it doesn&apos;t matter. The pack (of</div><div>two) leaped across Lee Highway and up into a wooded playground</div><div>clearing before maneuvering through a neighborhood towards a power</div><div>line easement. Another patch of woods held a beer check next to some</div><div>old civil war earthworks. The hares offered a fine assortment of</div><div>quality beers including a themed selection of Devil&apos;s Backbone</div><div>&apos;Azrael&apos; (Angel of Death). However the pack only drank one beer before</div><div>moving on.... The next morning I went to pick the check up and it was a</div><div>frozen block of ice and beer! Kept cold all day in my car! Trail</div><div>headed into and out of a stream valley and back briefly through some</div><div>neighborhoods before delving back down into another hollow with a</div><div>rising water level. Some fun log crossings and a slip-slidy hill side</div><div>provided the pack with some fun terrain before following Willow Spring</div><div>Run under a tunnel. Lucky for the pack, the tunnel offered some brief</div><div>relief from the snow that was now coming down hard! Also lucky for the</div><div>pack was the fact that the water level in the tunnel lessened the</div><div>muck-level of the mud at the bottom. The trail continued through the</div><div>woods along the creek side, through some brambles and smack into..... a</div><div>Back Check 10. The wankers told us later they just sat and stared at</div><div>for a minute, cursing us under their breaths. Back to the tunnel and</div><div>up onto the road they went before crossing Lee Highway again to begin</div><div>snaking through a subdivision and diving into Willow Springs Run Park.</div><div>You know those little stepping stones they put at creeks to walk</div><div>across safely? Yeah, those were under water! Trail continued to twist</div><div>along the path and was supposed to circle around a retention pond</div><div>towards the second beer check, that only the wily-wankers who didn&apos;t</div><div>do the trail (as laid) partook in after we showed them where it was</div><div>(and marked it). Oh well, at least they got some beer finally. The</div><div>two-pack however kept on going straight and bypassed it before finally</div><div>zig-zagging up a power line easement on in. The wintry mix now falling</div><div>fairly steadily we decided to forgo standing outside any longer and we</div><div>all sallied forth to Red Rock&apos;s Caf? for end!</div><div>It was poker night at Red Rocks but we decided to take over a few</div><div>tables on the other side of the bar since we looked like a bunch of</div><div>homeless people (except Horse Jerker, who lives across the street and</div><div>ran home quick to get a shower before joining us!) I got us some</div><div>Nachos and AndHowsHerBush ordered a few pitchers and we started doing</div><div>what hashers do best... drinking and gabbing! We needled Just Austin for</div><div>stories to save as tidbits when it comes to naming time, we shared</div><div>stories of the trail (or lack of in some of the wankers case), and we</div><div>toasted our camaraderie in stupidity by hanging outside and running</div><div>through creeks and woods on such a SH!TTY night! I had to leave after</div><div>I scarfed down some quick tacos, so someone else will have to tell you</div><div>which local Centreville-Cougars tried to take Bad Dog home.</div><div><br></div><div>Those of you that stayed at home all nice and snuggled up missed a</div><div>great trail! Can&apos;t wait to use it again when the trees and thorns are</div><div>all in full bloom again! On-On, Taster&apos;s Choice!</div><div><br></div><div>See you on April 22nd when Parent&apos;s Weekend and the other SH!T Jews do</div><div>a late Passover run (because they were all celebrating Passover last</div><div>week and missed trail!) He promises it won&apos;t be the Cluster-F*ck that</div><div>last years 8 mile debacle was. Silver Lining is involved so hopefully</div><div>that lends some credibility and she will keep them from getting</div><div>schwasted before laying trail! (don&apos;t hold your breath on that one!)</div>', ''),
(1253, 629, '<div>So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers Trail #628</div><div>The Anal 10 Plagues (shots) of Passover Trail!</div><div>Hares: "Parent&apos;s Weekend", "Herpicles"</div><div><br></div><div>Location: A church on Braddock Rd in Fairfax, West of Ox Rd and East</div><div>of Shirley Gate... (Name of church has been redacted to avoid this page</div><div>showing up on the Google Search for it!)</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>And How&apos;s Her Bush</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Tasters Choice</div><div>Vaginger Monologues</div><div>Nuclear Jism</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Anti-I</div><div>Strokin My Wife Away</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>The Little C*ck That Won&apos;t</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Dr. Stranglove</div><div>Cheap Ass Gigolo</div><div>IOWAtchin My Family</div><div>Mark Twaint</div><div>Loves The C*ck (Visitor from Tel Aviv!)</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>Ginger Southern Comfort (First-time SH*T Hasher!)</div><div>Amber Alert</div><div>Just Austin</div><div>Just John</div><div>Just Jenny (Parent&apos;s Weekend&apos;s Sister)</div><div>Just Courtney (~ First-time SH*T Hasher who came with Ginger Southern Comfort)</div><div><br></div><div>After last week&apos;s frozen rainy escapades only a few miles away (on the</div><div>ACTUAL day of Passover) all the fairweather (weak!) hashers came out</div><div>to enjoy another trail in Fairfax. A late afternoon storm cleared up</div><div>just in time and we had some great weather for the trail that awaited</div><div>us! For all 2 of you that actually read these, I forgot to mention</div><div>last week that I hared trail wearing ER wrist band, a token from an</div><div>early morning visit that day where I was diagnosed with</div><div>Conjunctivitis... I promised not to touch anyone and nobody showed up</div><div>this week with Pink-Eye so I&apos;m glad I avoided any violations for</div><div>trying to spread disease through the hash!</div><div><br></div><div>Herp and Parent&apos;s Weekend teamed up again (cue horror film shrieks) as</div><div>is their custom this time of year to force us to recognize their</div><div>religious leanings by reliving the 10 plagues of Pesach (Passover).</div><div>The hash-spin on this is that the plagues are presented to us in a</div><div>symbolic fashion as Shot Checks! You might recall last year&apos;s debacle</div><div>(I can&apos;t really even call it a trail) an 8+ mile death march in the</div><div>Wakefield area (This is Passover... not the exodus!) where most of the</div><div>hashers just gave up and headed back to start due to lack of flour and</div><div>questionable checks. You see the problem is that these two usually</div><div>get fershnickered over the course of a few hours before trail... this</div><div>isn&apos;t too bad unless it&apos;s when they are the ones responsible for</div><div>laying the trail! This year they did the same thing.... But only after</div><div>they prelaid at least half the trail. So it wasn&apos;t the jacked up</div><div>abortion of a trail we have come to love and expect from these</div><div>menches. How do I know it was pre-layed you ask? Because the flour was</div><div>wet after about the first  1/4  mile, meaning it had been there before the</div><div>quick rainstorm! Another clue was when they both very conspicuously</div><div>ran past the pack (waiting to head out on trail) down Braddock in a</div><div>direction that was not where trail was (so they could link up to the</div><div>end of their pre-laid section and continue laying trail. So anyway....</div><div><br></div><div>We gathered around in the parking lot of a church and met some new</div><div>faces, Loves the C*ock from Tel Aviv H3 in Israel who was in the area</div><div>for work and picked a fitting hash to attend, Ginger Southern</div><div>Comfort, a transplant from the Los Cruces H3 in New Mexico, and his</div><div>girlfriend Just Courtney, a virgin who he had talked into coming out</div><div>to run. It finally warmed up enough for IOWA and Mark Twaint to come</div><div>back and spend some time with us too! And Just Austin returned... note</div><div>people that he has hared and has been out regularly for enough</div><div>trails.. a naming could be coming soon!</div><div>The hares described that the shots would be marked with a flour Star</div><div>of David (described irreverently by the hares as two triangles</div><div>f*cking). The directions to find the shots were to "look left, look</div><div>right, look up, look down, l&apos;chaim!" (say it out loud... its makes more</div><div>sense)</div><div><br></div><div>When the time arrived most of the pack headed off in the direction the</div><div>true-trail arrow pointed.... But Amber Alert headed off in the direction</div><div>we saw the Hares go by earlier when they tried to sneak by and he was</div><div>followed by Ginger Southern Comfort, who ditched his girlfriend,</div><div>leaving her alone with the pack! We&apos;ll get to them later... because</div><div>they never found any trail and ended up back-tracking and doing trail</div><div>alone in the dark! Seriously, who Zens from start when you are at a</div><div>pack you have never ran with and don&apos;t know where you are??</div><div><br></div><div>I won&apos;t describe trail in my usual manner because I fully intend to</div><div>steal portions of it for a future trail! However I will try a new</div><div>method of describing what we saw and went through.</div><div><br></div><div>Woods, Teepees made out of sticks... hard to tell if it was a homeless</div><div>dude&apos;s pad or the place the local kids meet for their beer and cigs.</div><div>Past a Golf Driving Range.... Watch out for errant balls! (snicker</div><div>snicker) . Down into a stream valley, up out of a stream valley, back</div><div>into the stream valley! Shots up in the sky! No seriously... the hares</div><div>climbed up a deer hunter&apos;s tree stand and put one of the shots there!</div><div>Fork in the stream and a check but we found trail and continued on for</div><div>a half mile before climbing out of the shiggy and onto some pavement</div><div>for a short period. Walkers split off and caught back up with us a</div><div>mile and half later. Runner&apos;s headed up a long incline before diving</div><div>back into some woods and a series of checks that kept going straight.</div><div>Shortly after the second mile trail continued up a hill, but knowing</div><div>where we were I suspected a back-check as we passed a perpendicular</div><div>trail. AndHowsHer took the bait and I split off to find the true trail</div><div>shortly after... I think it was a back-check 9 or 13... the Hares had said</div><div>13 was a mystical number to the Jews so expect lots of those... but</div><div>there weren&apos;t that many actually! We followed some twisting trails for</div><div>about half a mile and then plunged creek-valley-swamp.... Literally,</div><div>Some SERIOUS Mud here folks. The sun was starting to set and darkness</div><div>was creeping in. The cooler weather following the storm created some</div><div>fog in some of the low-lying areas of the shiggy which sucked for me</div><div>because I was wearing glasses and they kept fogging up! It&apos;s hard to</div><div>bushwack through shiggy with no sight... I fell a few times, but luckily</div><div>no one saw. At this point I was the FRB and I went crotch deep in one</div><div>hidden spot, luckily as I pulled out of the mud and continued up a</div><div>hill out of the valley I kept quiet and heard Just Austin fall in too!</div><div>Aunti-I was just behind him and was able to avoid the same fate.</div><div>Apparently when AHHB fell in the same hole it was quite the dramatic</div><div>event, complete with flailing arms and school-girl shrieks! The next</div><div>half a mile gave us some more good shiggy and then all of a sudden we</div><div>burst out onto the road and could see start across the street. I was</div><div>kind enough to let Just Austin rush past me to the Finish to claim his</div><div>FRB Title! About 3.6 miles of some great shiggy, fun checks, and 10</div><div>delicious shots! So then we waited.... And walkers came in.... but we</div><div>still had several running pack members (the ones who had decided to</div><div>try and snare the hares but failed) out still. Just Courtney started</div><div>to get worried because she had the keys and Ginger Southern Comfort</div><div>wasn&apos;t answering his phone, but finally after some discussion as to</div><div>how we were gonna go out and find the guy who hadn&apos;t followed trail as</div><div>it was.... He strolled in! He really just made it too easy to violate as</div><div>you will see later.</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: "Just Austin"</div><div>FBI: "Aunti-I"</div><div>DFL: "IOWAtching My Family"</div><div><br></div><div>Returners: "IOWAtching My Family", "Mark Twant", "Silver Lining",</div><div>"Parent&apos;s Weekend", "Just Jenny", "Herpicles"</div><div><br></div><div>Analversaries: "Amber Alert" (14), "Just Just (John)" (7), "Cheap Ass</div><div>Gigolo" (7), "Parent&apos;s Weekend" (140)</div><div><br></div><div>Violations: (from AHHB, I didn&apos;t take any notes and forgot most of it!)</div><div><br></div><div>1.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"Just Jenny": Playing Harps w/ears.</div><div>2.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>HARES: a) Prelaying trail, b) Laying a Good Prelaid Trail, c)</div><div>Openly Gay Hashing, and d) Fish in Beard.</div><div>3.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"All The Way In": For NOT being FRB. (he was taking his time and</div><div>enjoying the Shot Checks... or was he enjoying the harreittes?)</div><div>4.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Many: For &apos;Mud Bathing&apos;!!</div><div>5.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"All The Way In": Trading One Harriette for Two.</div><div>6.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"Ginger Southern Comfort": Leaving a virgin Harriette Behind.</div><div>7.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"Bad Dog": For NOT being DFL.</div><div>8.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>RA: Loosing His Ship?</div><div>9.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"Vaginger Monologues": Poor Taste... However, She Drank ALL of the Shots!!</div><div>10.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>"Little C*ck That Won&apos;t", and " IOWAtching My Family": Non-Wife</div><div>Swap - Shit Swap?</div><div><br></div><div>Last week&apos;s Hash-Sh*t went to "Department of Vegetative Affairs" for</div><div>being &apos;drunk and disorderly&apos;... or because she spilt her beer at the end</div><div>of all the nominations!! But she didn&apos;t come out this week so we</div><div>couldn&apos;t pass it on!</div><div><br></div><div>The pack moved on after circle to Brion&apos;s Grille, but I had to bolt so</div><div>I hope they had fun. We were just there two weeks ago so they know</div><div>what to expect! Hopefully we&apos;ll see Ginger Southern Comfort and Just</div><div>Courtney again assuming we didn&apos;t scare them off with our crazy</div><div>outside-the-beltway antics!</div><div><br></div><div>So overall, Herp and Parent&apos;s trail was actually really good! Some</div><div>great terrain, well-marked, and no shortage of shots for all! Great</div><div>Job boys.... You have proven you can do it, so no excuses next time! So</div><div>sign up again on the hare-line and prove the nay-sayers wrong!</div><div><br></div><div>On-on,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div>', ''),
