(1255, 631, '<div>Trail #630:</div><div>The Seis De Mayo Trail!</div><div>May 6, 2014</div><div><br></div><div>Start: Fairfax, VA (in the city)</div><div><br></div><div>Hares:</div><div>Vaginger Monologues</div><div>Just (Just) John</div><div><br></div><div>Attendees:</div><div>All the Way In</div><div>Deer Penthouse</div><div>DeVA</div><div>Parent&apos;s Weekend</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Amber Alert</div><div>Stroken My Wife Away</div><div>Cheap Ass Gigalo</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div><br></div><div>VISITORS:</div><div>Tiny Two Stroke - Smutty Crab visitor</div><div>Beef Curtains - Iwakuni (Japan) White Snake H3 visitor</div><div><br></div><div>JUSTS:</div><div>Just Mark - visitor</div><div>Just Natalie - visitor</div><div>Just Tara W. - Friend of Lush of the Irish</div><div>Just Scott - Friend of Lush</div><div>Just Austin</div><div><br></div><div>VIRGIN:</div><div>Just Kelly Beth</div><div><br></div><div>We gathered to run off our Cinco De Mayo hangovers (or if you are like</div><div>me and had to work the night before getting ready for the next day&apos;s!)</div><div>in the back of a little professional office park in Fairfax City. Some</div><div>ol&apos; biddy came out and started telling us we couldn&apos;t be there because</div><div>it was private property... we glanced around for signs denoting it as</div><div>such, cameras that would record us, and anything that might give us</div><div>the inkling that we couldn&apos;t be there.... There was none so we smiled</div><div>and continued out activities. This was Just John&apos;s virgin haring but</div><div>he obviously had hared already because the flour on his legs gave it</div><div>away. It was nice to see him in running clothes for once though!</div><div>Vaginger was freaking out between the lady saying she would call the</div><div>cops and how trail was going to be.... I just told her to relax, take a</div><div>deep breath, and let it happen... wait that sounded creepy. Either way</div><div>we had a great pack of visitors, the regulars, and even a Virgin! Just</div><div>Kelly-Beth works for a local university (not to be named!) for</div><div>admissions and owns a CrossFit Box on the side. She found out about us</div><div>from some friends who knows who had hashed overseas and looked us up</div><div>on the internet. She seemed to enjoy the hashing attitude and</div><div>camaraderie on trail and after so hopefully we&apos;ll see her again.</div><div>TinyTwoStroke, from SMUTTY out in SE Maryland brought his buddy Beef</div><div>Curtains who was in town for work from Japan. Lush and Stab told two</div><div>friends Just Mark and Natalie to show up for the hash.... But didn&apos;t</div><div>come themselves so we had to babysit them for them!</div><div><br></div><div>It was a great trail, my GPS zonked out on me so I can&apos;t give too much</div><div>detail other than I recall there were no shortage of dick and boob</div><div>checks, our visitors and virgins took full advantage of them. Beer</div><div>Check was in a nice secluded stream valley with themed drinks like</div><div>Margarita Mixers and Mexican Beer. Kudos to the hares for finding the</div><div>shiggy they could in the middle of downtown Fairfax! I&apos;m guessing it</div><div>was about 3.5 miles total, with some great checks that really stumped</div><div>the pack for a bit! Virginia once again showed me how hilly of a bitch</div><div>she can be! So we ran on into circle and proceeded to get loud and</div><div>rowdy as we violated each other and then closed out with some</div><div>namings!!!</div><div><br></div><div>NAMINGS!!!</div><div>It was time for a Double Header! (Head.. who said head?....) We were</div><div>able to get in the naming of both Just Just John and Just Austin .</div><div><br></div><div>Just John&apos;s Doctoral Degree is in theater and his dissertation was on</div><div>the use of Zombies on the American stage. He also is known for having</div><div>&apos;relations&apos; on walker&apos;s trail..... there were other names but we decided</div><div>upon "The Walking Head".</div><div><br></div><div>Just Austin, a Hokie with a Doctorate in mathematics (Seriously how</div><div>are we attracting all these intellectuals to the hash?) who had a</div><div>dissertation that&apos;s title was so long even he couldn&apos;t remember it....</div><div>Anyway A few really good names came up including Texas Instruments ,</div><div>and my favorite, Reverse Polish Cowgirl, but in the end it was "Dr.</div><div>Cockulus".</div><div><br></div><div>So I can&apos;t recall who got the HashShit... or any other violations... I</div><div>blame the extended beer check! I do remember that Just Natalie was</div><div>very much enjoying circle and took the place of Lush who usually yells</div><div>into the circle. Hope to see some of our new friends again and on-on!</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>(last week&apos;s trash coming later this week, along with tonights!)</div>', ''),
(1256, 632, '<div>Trail #631</div><div>The "Italian, Russian Virgin" or OldManShortShorts Trail</div><div>Hare: AndHowsHerBush</div><div>Location: Ashburn</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>Little Cock The Won&apos;t</div><div>The Otter Pink Meat</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>The Udder Ho</div><div>Spitz.cum</div><div>Pyro</div><div>Parent&apos;s Weekend</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>Suckled2Bee</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>Dr. Cockulus</div><div>No Name Nyet</div><div>Doc Strangelove</div><div>Cheap Ass Gigolo</div><div>Virgins:</div><div>Just Drew (PW and Silver&apos;s soon to be Brother-in-law)</div><div>Just Valentin (NoName&apos;s Russian Gal Pal)</div><div>Just Elly (NoName&apos;s Russian Gal Pal)</div><div><br></div><div>As we gathered in the commuter lot on the Russel Branch Parkway just</div><div>off Route 7, the was a beautiful blue to east..... however to the west</div><div>was dark grey and full of lightening. We were in a limbo between two</div><div>worlds... one that promised sunshine and happiness... and one that</div><div>foretold of a dangerous journey through a monsoon. Can you guess which</div><div>direction AndHowsHerBush took us?</div><div><br></div><div>As trail dived directly into some pretty serious shiggy and took us up</div><div>and down the steep banks of Broad Run, the pack could be heard</div><div>uttering curses to the hare as he took us into the coming storm and</div><div>through some good thorns and prickers. We hooked north and came onto a</div><div>tunnel under Russell Branch Rd where we found our First Beer Check. We</div><div>didn&apos;t stop too long because the rain had gone from light drizzle to</div><div>big honkin drops. Meanwhile the pack enjoyed listening to</div><div>LongTimeNoSeer Otter shoot down Bad Dog&apos;s attempts at laying down the</div><div>mack... it never gets old! We made our way up to Route 7 and what we</div><div>thought went over... but trail was located in another tunnel with... MORE</div><div>Beer! The rain reaaaaaly started coming down hard so we hunkered down,</div><div>drank some more beer and drew obscene chalk markings on the roof of</div><div>the tunnel... pretty certain they won&apos;t wash away until the global</div><div>warming stuff happens and the entire area is submerged! After a good</div><div>long wait, MOST of us headed out to continue... we figured we needed to</div><div>get going before the whole trail was washed away. A series of tricky</div><div>checks along Bridgefield Way slowed us down but flour was found as we</div><div>wound our way through a subdivision. By now the rain had pretty much</div><div>stopped and we just enjoyed the mushy mud and puddles it left us! We</div><div>dashed back into the shiggy behind some apartments and then were once</div><div>again calling on-on to the confused apartment dwellers. All of sudden</div><div>I recognized our location... we had done a big damn circle and were back</div><div>at the tunnel under 7. A true Trail arrow pointed back towards the</div><div>tunnel but the pack wasn&apos;t convinced. I ventured through to check out</div><div>but realized no one could hear me over the sounds of the busy highway</div><div>so I used my high powered rape whistle to let them know what I had</div><div>found.... Parent&apos;s weekend, Just Drew, and Pyro chilling out with the</div><div>Beer that they had pulled out of the tunnel after apparently &apos;snaring&apos;</div><div>AHHB who came back through expecting the pack to have left the check!</div><div>He told them to go do a loop and then they just moved the beer and</div><div>kept drinking (You can guess how coherent this left PW at circle!) So</div><div>I grabbed another beer and waited for the pack to roll up before</div><div>heading out through the shiggy and into/across a field of waist high</div><div>grass back towards start. Luckily that kind of grass lends itself to</div><div>be easy to follow where the hare had been.. so I think my GPS tracked</div><div>the fastest part of the whole trail there. We burst out of the field</div><div>and across the commuter lot to start for a great finish to a nice 2.5</div><div>mile trail. AHHB did an outstanding job of giving us some good ol&apos;</div><div>SoHappy Shiggy, Hare tricks, and multiple opportunities for beer!</div><div>Thanks Old Man! We all gathered in and enjoyed the after-storm</div><div>weather, charged our vessels and proceeded to violate each other.... I</div><div>know I have said it before... these trashes are way funnier when I have</div><div>the ability to write them soon after they happen because the</div><div>violations make sense! And I recall the back stories... I will endeavor</div><div>to fail you less in the future (probably not though!)</div><div><br></div><div>Violations!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Dr. Cockulus</div><div>FBI: Silver Lining</div><div>DFL: Parent&apos;s Just Drew, and Pyro</div><div><br></div><div>Returners:</div><div>Otter, Spitz, Pyro, Suckled (thats sounds funny when you say it fast)</div><div><br></div><div>Silver Lining - for Having tiny hand syndrome and only able to hold 3</div><div>balls (of the cheesey variety) at once!</div><div>Parent&apos;s Just Drew, and Pyro - for skipping most of trail and drinking</div><div>most of the beer!</div><div>AHHB - For trying to get the pack killed during a torrential downpour</div><div>and lightning storm!</div><div>Otter - For trying an Air Dunk on trail.... Not like Mike!</div><div>Silver Lining - for taunting Jesus on trail during the storm!</div><div>Parent&apos;s, Just Drew and Pyro - for coming in AFTER Bad Dog</div><div>Suckled2B - for showing Amazonian Strength w/ dead trees on trail</div><div>Suckled2B - for being worried about sex in the Kitchen on trail!</div><div>Otter - for letting herself go!</div><div>AHHB - for being such a crusty old mad that he was arguing with</div><div>himself about how he laid the trail</div><div><br></div><div>Somebody got the hashit... yeah it didn&apos;t get written down. Maybe when I</div><div>write next week&apos;s trash I&apos;ll remember!</div><div><br></div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div>', ''),
(1257, 633, '<div>Trail #632</div><div>Your Mothers Trail...Short Flat and Dry</div><div>Harea: Deer Penthouse and DeVa</div><div>Location: Springfield</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>Little Cock The Won&apos;t</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Parent&apos;s Weekend</div><div>Mind The Gap</div><div>Stab My Cock</div><div>Rosary Bleeds</div><div>DoLayMe</div><div>How Big Is Your Flower</div><div>The S&amp;M Man</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Mark Twaint</div><div>Iowatching my Family</div><div>Cheap Ass Gigolo</div><div>Silver Lining</div><div>Dr Strangelove</div><div>Horse Jerker</div><div>Just Mark</div><div><br></div><div>Unlike the week prior for AHHB&apos;s run, we had gorgeous weather for this</div><div>trail. If only the pack could find where it started! The hares had</div><div>done some intense googling and spouted out an address they thought was</div><div>the start... however most GPS apps and map programs spat that address</div><div>out across Old Keene Mill Rd a half mile south. Luckily most of us are</div><div>such beer-crazy nitwits we just kept driving around until we say</div><div>wankers. I had to make an emergency update to PudJam just in case</div><div>someone actually called it! Eventually the pack made it and we kicked</div><div>D-Va and DP off to go lay each other... err trail.</div><div><br></div><div>We took off behind the Huntsman Blvd pool and into the woods before</div><div>crossing Pohick Creek and ambling south along it till we hit what I</div><div>think was a Back-check 27 or something. It added almost a half mile to</div><div>trail through shiggy. I&apos;ll tell you what Hares, that&apos;s one way to make</div><div>the pack question every bit of flour you put down when you hit us with</div><div>a whopper like that right out of the gate! (well played evil hares!)</div><div><br></div><div>We continued back across Pohick Creek and proceeded to bounce back and</div><div>forth over it for a mile and half. Somewhere in there we hit a boob</div><div>check and Bad Dog insisted that Silver show her goods. She replied</div><div>with a F you, and we decided that Cheap Ass Gigolo would suffice as he</div><div>had the biggest ones there. Stab My Cock meanwhile was scaring off (or</div><div>trying to mate with) Deer (not Deer Penthouse) and found trail. We hit</div><div>a Runner&apos;s Walker split at a power line easement and I was feeling the</div><div>effects of poor body lubrication during the weekend&apos;s 1/2 marathon and</div><div>decided to do walkers trail from there on out. so I guess I was a FWB.</div><div>The Runners added another 1-2 miles of pretty good soul sucking shiggy</div><div>I am told. The Walkers trail continued up and down and up and down (it</div><div>was a little hilly) the easement heading south towards Old keene Mill</div><div>for almost a mile. Here it joined back up with runners and across to a</div><div>power station where there was a BN... in SH!T that means the end is near</div><div>not Beer Check! So being the first to it I just kept on running</div><div>instead of looking for beer, thinking that I was almost at the</div><div>end....trail continued up the easement before busting out onto a road.</div><div>Another half mile down the road before we ran alongside the Western</div><div>edge of Greentree Village park (shame on you hares or passing up some</div><div>good shiggy!). Back on Old Keene Mill I stalked up on D-Va (hindsight,</div><div>I totally should have goosed her!) who was happily laying the last  1/4 </div><div>mile of trail as we turned north and into a retention pond area....</div><div>"Shit where does trail go from here?" she said... "I don&apos;t know... you are</div><div>the hare!?" luckily end was just a few hundred yards away in an old</div><div>basketball court clearing. She said "wait right here, I&apos;ll go get the</div><div>bag vehicle".... Then I waited... and waited... for like 15 minutes before</div><div>DP showed up and then another 5 and AHHB pulled in. We got the beer</div><div>all set up and finally some walkers showed up, and after a good while,</div><div>the rest of the pack trickled in. For walkers, overall 3.6 miles of</div><div>good trail. Runner&apos;s you are on your own there! It was very much dark</div><div>by the time circle started so we grabbed out beers and headlamps and</div><div>started talking shit!</div><div><br></div><div>Violations!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: ATWI</div><div>FBI: Taster&apos;s Choice (for having a vagina and walking second half and</div><div>actually being first in)</div><div>DFL: Bad Dog</div><div><br></div><div>SH!T Virgin: Rosary Bleeds!</div><div><br></div><div>Returners:</div><div>Mind The Gap</div><div>Stab My Cock</div><div>DoLayMe</div><div>How Big Is Your Flower</div><div>The S&amp;M Man</div><div><br></div><div>Hares: Directions to Start where actually to A prime.... But not the A&apos;</div><div>that end was at!!</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice: Forgetting baby powder to soothe the pain from</div><div>running the  1/2  marathon on Sunday, and having to walk second half!)</div><div>Hares: Not enough boob-checks</div><div>How Big is Your Flour: Technology on trail.... Trudging through the</div><div>water and shiggy while simultaneously using your smartphone to order a</div><div>bridesmaid dress!</div><div>Mind The Gap: For being scared of the Easter Bunny</div><div>DoLayMe: fell in the mud and said she didn&apos;t mind because she loves swampass</div><div>LittleCock: For asking Mind The Gap&apos; name for the sole purpose of</div><div>violating her and not getting a number in the process!</div><div>DVa- for curbing Deer Penthouses Truck.</div><div><br></div><div>and again... we gave the hashit to somebody... if only it had been written down!</div><div>I went home and had a dream I had it... but I looked in my garage and</div><div>couldn&apos;t find it so I don&apos;t think it was me!</div><div><br></div><div>The hares were nice enough to shuttle us back and forth to the start,</div><div>where I proceeded to leave my keys, my chair, and my bag of dirty hash</div><div>clothes in their truck/truck bed... luckily they came back... twice! It</div><div>did however amuse Parent&apos;s Weekend to watch me frantically checking my</div><div>bag for the keys which it turned out.... Where in my bag all along.</div><div><br></div><div>On-half-of-a-half-mind-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div>', ''),
(1258, 634, '<div>Trail #633</div><div>The "Another Lovely Springfield Trail" Trail</div><div><br></div><div>Hares: Doc Strangelove and Cheap Ass Gigolo</div><div><br></div><div>Location: South Run Park (How the hell is this Springfield??</div><div>Apparently it is. I&apos;d say Burke though!)</div><div><br></div><div>Pack:</div><div>Little Cock The Won&apos;t</div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div><div>All The Way In</div><div>Rosary Bleeds</div><div>Bad Dog</div><div>Parents Weekend</div><div>Amber Alert</div><div><br></div><div>I had fun recording the PudJam announcement for this week, but I must</div><div>have slurred too much because hardly anybody showed up! According to</div><div>the Directions we were to "Look for wankers milling around." Well</div><div>Parent&apos;s Weekend and I drove in and kept looking for Wankers... there</div><div>were plenty of kids and soccer milfs but no wankers. The park was in</div><div>full swing soccer mode this evening... we kept going, weaving through</div><div>the parking lot looking for the last hidden area, the usual hang out</div><div>of wankers. We found a little empty gravel lot behind a storage shed</div><div>and figured that was good enough. We found Little Cock there, soon</div><div>joined by ATWI and Rosary Bleeds. So now we had Wankers milling</div><div>around... it must be start! Then Doc drove up and said we were wrong...</div><div>Parent&apos;s pointed out that Little Cock has the beer therefor wherever</div><div>he was was right! Doc insisted though and we all drove back to the</div><div>entrance to a spot right along the main road in full sight of the</div><div>soccer games and parked next to an angry looking soccer mom (not a</div><div>milf) and waited for start. Said soccer mom didn&apos;t seem to enjoy the</div><div>loud, obnoxious and sometimes vulgar conversations that the</div><div>sausage-fest of pack was having so we toned it down for a minute then</div><div>forgot and got loud again. Needless to say, this hash seems to have</div><div>found itself lately in an on-again/off-again relationship with Mother</div><div>Nature. What I mean is every other week we have some craptastic</div><div>weather on Tuesday followed by gorgeous weather the next! Not to be</div><div>outdone by AndHowsHerBush&apos;s trail of two weeks ago Doc and Cheap Ass</div><div>Gigolo found a way to wrangle in more rain and bigger lightening this</div><div>week. Had trail chosen to go south we would have been scott-free as</div><div>the weather moved along north of us... but what fun would that have</div><div>been!</div><div><br></div><div>The Hares ran off and scared us right off the bat when Cheap Ass</div><div>Gigolo started asking Doc what the marks meant again! Later when we</div><div>headed out we bounded deeper into the park before crossing a little a</div><div>strip of shiggy and out into a power easement, heading southwest</div><div>towards a beautiful sunset filled sky... but as they say on VH1&apos;s behind</div><div>the music "And then things went sour".... we hit a false trail and had</div><div>to head north uphill with Armageddon happening before us. Lightening</div><div>and rain was easily seen and heard falling not on us, but where we</div><div>were headed. We clipped back into the woods for bit slowed down by</div><div>some logs and curious placement of flour. As we reached the edge of</div><div>the woods on the Fairfax County Parkway the heavy drops of thunderous</div><div>rain pelted us as we broke the tree line. Off we tore being very very</div><div>f&apos;in careful across the parkway and into the power line easement.</div><div>Thoroughly soaked and not even a mile in, we dodged lightning strikes</div><div>that boomed just moments after flashing (always a good sign right??)</div><div>while we attempted to find rapidly dissolving flour. We continued for</div><div>over a mile over a few creeks that crossed the easement and through</div><div>some checks that slowed us up momentarily before ducking back into the</div><div>woods at Middle Run Park, I enjoyed the brief respite from immediate</div><div>electrical death, but the rain was still coming down hard under the</div><div>canopy. Trail took us along Cherry run and we were delighted to find a</div><div>bucket of beers inside a tunnel. As it seemed safer for the moment</div><div>inside the tunnel we stopped and waited for the pack to catch up. They</div><div>didn&apos;t really though... and we figured they had ditched trail to head</div><div>back to start or shortcutted so after several moments (and a hare</div><div>sighting at the end of the long tunnel) we took off through the tunnel</div><div>and down along the creekside. The hare really tricked us up by doing a</div><div>giant swirly loop on us against the backs of trees. We then caught him</div><div>and realized he had lost himself trying to relay flour and ran with us</div><div>out of the park and into a neighborhood before dropping us back into</div><div>some pretty extreme shiggy along Peyton run till we finally caught up</div><div>with Cheap Ass Gigolo! We had just done a mile and half loop to a spot</div><div>only a few hundred feet away from where we caught Doc so he could give</div><div>CAG chance to finish laying to beer check.... Drat you Wiley hares!!!</div><div>But it was some great shiggy so I couldn&apos;t be too mad. We came upon</div><div>the second beer check which was in a tunnel underneath Huntsman Blvd</div><div>and let the hares run off to finish trail. We had beer, the rain had</div><div>let up, what else was there to do.... But as we sat drinking the beers,</div><div>we started noticing the water level was rising, and pretty rapidly as</div><div>all the runoff from the entire area made its way through where we were</div><div>standing to Huntsman Lake on the other side of the tunnel!! Since ATWI</div><div>doesn&apos;t do beer, he was content to start tearing apart the beaver dam</div><div>and aid the rushing water as it continued continue to grow. Parent&apos;s</div><div>Weekend kept trying to convince me to slide on my ass to the end of</div><div>the tunnel as the current was getting pretty strong, but after a big</div><div>ass log careened past us on the rapids and the beer bucket almost</div><div>washed away we decided it was time to move on! Trail crossed over the</div><div>road and down into the dried out (kinda) lakebed of Huntsman Lake.... It</div><div>was pretty mushy and you had to really try to find the more solid</div><div>spots to avoid going knee deep, I&apos;m pretty sure I heard PW bite it but</div><div>I was too busy fending for myself to look back. We ringed the SE</div><div>corner of the lake and popped up a hill onto a trail that brought back</div><div>to the parkway where the rain was picking up again. From here on out,</div><div>trail basically headed west along the parkway and then into South Run</div><div>park back to start. The rain had caused all the soccer games to get</div><div>cancelled and the area was pretty empty, except for a group of wet,</div><div>muddy hashers gathered around a few vehicles! Apparently AHHB had</div><div>stopped by and bolted. Booo! I had a tally of about 5.2 miles over an</div><div>hour and half period. Despite the possibility of instant death from</div><div>the great god Zeus up in the clouds, confused hares, and quickly</div><div>dissipating flour, the trail was a great shiggariffic tour of the</div><div>area. Some fun conversations were held at the beer check and I&apos;m</div><div>surprised none of us got hurt! We had a quick but sweet circle, mainly</div><div>due to Bad Dog wanting to violate everyone!</div><div><br></div><div>Violations!</div><div><br></div><div>FRB: Rosary Bleeds</div><div>FBI: Taster&apos;s Choice (somebody had to be it.. and I had the nicest legs)</div><div>DFL: Bad Dog</div><div><br></div><div>Returners:</div><div>Amber Alert</div><div><br></div><div>ATWI - For renaming Iowatchin&apos; to Ohionation on last week&apos;s signup!</div><div>Hares - for making a female unfriendly hash</div><div>Hares - for passing by all the nice tree bark and using puddles to</div><div>place their flour for trail!</div><div>Parents Weekend RA - cause the weather sucks</div><div>ATWI - for Pounding beaver (dams) on trail</div><div>Hares - for putting beer check in flood zones</div><div>Rosary Bleeds - for doing 9 trails in 6 days and still not knowing any</div><div>hash songs!</div><div><br></div><div>And to Bad Dog&apos;s credit he did run the trail with Mt Vernon&apos;s Hashit</div><div>if anyone out there was wondering!</div><div>See you at our Tour Du Hash trail on 10 June! I&apos;m busy for Otter&apos;s</div><div>birthday trail ?</div><div>On-On,</div><div><br></div><div>Taster&apos;s Choice</div>', ''),
